<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-Zubov Arrest,0180 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Stars' playerZubov arrested, accused of assaulting wife
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   COPPELL, Texas (AP) _ Dallas Stars defenseman Sergei Zubov was
arrestd early Sunday on charges of assaulting his wife.
	   Zubov, 27, was charged with aggravated assault and family
violence, a second-degree felony.
	   It was not known if Zubov's wife, Irina, was injured.
	   Coppell police said they went to Zubov's house in the middle of
the night after someone at the home dialed 911 and hung up.
	   Police said officers determined that Zubov had exhibited a
deadly weapon _ which police refused to identify _ and they took
him into custody. The Russian player was released sometime Sunday,
a department dispatcher said.
	   The hockey team issued a three-sentence statement from general
manager Bob Gainey.
	   ``The Dallas Stars and the National Hockey League are
cooperating fully with the authorities and are offering our
assistance and support to both Sergei and Irina,'' Gainey's
statement read.
	   The club said it would have no further comment.
</TEXT>
