<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-Buried Alive </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Four-year-old girl buried alive
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ Police said Monday they had arrested a man
who buried alive his wife's four-year-old daughter, whom he
apparently hated because she had a different father.
	   The girl, Cao Thi Be, was found dead in a hole about 0.7 meters
(two feet) deep near her home last Tuesday in the central province
of Binh Thuan. An autopsy showed she died of suffocation.
	   Her parents, Pham Van Tho and Cao Thi Hiep were married seven
years ago, but the girl was fathered by another man when Tho was in
prison serving a five-year term for assault.
	   Tho, 33, hated and often beat Be, police said. On May 31, he
returned home drunk, beat his wife and took the child away. Police
believe he put her in the hole, dug by local people to catch
salamanders, and buried her.
	   Tho fled but was tracked down and arrested Sunday. Police said
that local people were outraged over the crime. 	   
</TEXT>
