<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Australia-France-Vietnam-Oil </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Anzoil signs protocol for Hanoi basin
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PERTH, Australia (AP) _ Anzoil has signed an agreement with
French company Maurel and Prom to participate in a production
sharing agreement in the Hanoi Basin in Vietnam.
	   Anzoil said Monday it will farm out 25 percent of the production
sharing contract to M and P for U.S. dlrs 16.66 million, which will
be put toward the costs of appraisal of the D14 gas field in the
Hanoi Basin including three new exploration wells.
	   Anzoil and M and P will also enter into a joint operating
agreement to govern their future working arrangement in the
contract, with Anzoil retaining an operator status.
	   The agreement follows the release of an independent technical
report in April which said gas and oil discoveries in the Hanoi
Basin were expected to contain 522 billion cubic feet of
recoverable gas and 19 million barrels of recoverable oil.
	   M and P holds significant interests in oil drilling operations
around the world, according to Anzoil.
	   ``Their presence and good standing in the Vietnamese community
will bring significant benefits to the Anzoil joint venture as it
prepares itself to become a substantial energy provider in
Vietnam,'' executive chairman Jaap Poll said.
	   He added that the new agreement, which is still subject to
approval by the Anzoil board and Vietnamese authorities, was a vote
of confidence in the project by a major overseas group. 	   
</TEXT>
