<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Panda </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Farmers pull sick panda from dangerous river bank
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ A farmer who spotted a sick panda moving
perilously close to the edge of a turbulent river dashed down the
bank and wrestled the animal to safety, the state-run Xinhua News
Agency reported Monday.
	   Yang Yanfang grabbed the panda and rolled down the riverbank
with it, breaking the fall a few meters (yards) above the rushing
water by grabbing a tree branch, Xinhua said. Other farmers helped
him to control the animal and send it to a local forestry bureau
for medical treatment.
	   Yang suffered cuts on his arms. The panda recovered and was
returned to the Labahe Nature Reserve in Sichuan province in
southwest China.
	   Sichuan is home to the roughly 1,000 endangered pandas remaining
in the wild in China.
</TEXT>
