<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Hong Kong-Stocks </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Shares prices close generally mixed
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (A) - Share prices in Hong Kong closed generally mixed
in light trading Monday.
	   The Hang Seng Index, the market's key indicator of blue chips,
rose 17.16 points, or 0.2 percent, to 8,586.63. On Friday, the
index gained 11.04 points.
	   Turnover amounted to 4.55 billion Hong Kong dollars (U.S. dlrs
583 million), compared with Friday's 3.48 billion Hong Kong dollars
(U.S. dlrs 445 million).
	   Brokers said share prices fell in the morning despite sharp
gains on Wall Street on Friday because market sentiment was
dampened by the weakness of the Japanese currency.
	   The yen, which breached the level of 140 to the U.S. dollar,
triggered a rise in Hong Kong's interbank market rates, as banks
feared more regional uncertainty.
	   Selective bargain-hunting late in the session sent the index
into positive territory, brokers said.
	   Among gainers, HSBC Holdings rose 4.00 Hong Kong dollars to
190.50, Hang Seng Bank rose 1.00 dollar to 51.75, and Hong Kong
Telecom rose 15 cents to 13.80.
	   Among losers, Sun Hung Kai Properties fell 70 cents to 34.00,
Cheung Kong fell 50 cents to 38.20, and Hutchison Whampoa fell 20
cents to 37.80.
</TEXT>
