<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SKorea-Subway Strike </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Seoul subway threatens to go on strike
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ Seoul's subway union theatened on
Monday to send its 9,000 members out on strike this week to press
for pay hikes and better working conditions.
	   The union said the indefinite strike will begin Wednesday unless
management accepts its demands for a 7.8 percent pay hike and a
reduction in work hours from the present 42 to 40 a week.
	   Management has rejected the demands, saying that the subway
keeps losing money.
	   Management asked the government's labor arbitration committee to
intervene but the union said it would not honor the committee's
role. In past labor disputes, the union rejected the committee as
pro-management.
	   Both sides said they would meet again Tuesday to try to avert
the strike.
</TEXT>
