w2555 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-China-FactoryBeating     06-08 0247
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Factory Beating </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
14 arrested for beatings at factory that killed 1, injured 6
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ Workers suspected of stealing three computer hard
disks at a Shenzhen electronics plant were beaten so severely that
one died and six others were seriously injured, state-run media
reported Monday.
	   Managers and guards at the Yida Electronics Co. plant tortured
the workers almost all day on May 20, beating them with iron and
wooden bars, flashlights and their fists, the China Daily reported.
	   Fourteen people, including Sun Shiqiang of Hong Kong, the
factory boss, and guards and managers of the company were arrested
and put before the public at a rally on June 3 in Shenzhen, the
Workers Daily reported. Shenzhen, a booming special economic zone,
borders Hong Kong.
	   The newspaper accounts said factory managers suspected worker Li
Chaozhan of stealing the computer parts, beat him severely and
forced him to implicate others.
	   Sun threatened to kill the workers and their families if they
did not confess, and also ordered others to throw Li's body out of
a second story window to make his death look like suicide, the
Workers' Daily reported.
	   China Daily said reports of physical attacks on workers at the
Yida plant ``have not been uncommon.''
	   It quoted Zhang Qiwen, a local Communist Party official, as
saying the case showed that some business people do not understand
or do not respect the laws and cannot control their guards.
</TEXT>
