 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   The chairman of one of Singapore's biggest banks warned of a
recession next year if the government does not take action now to
stimulate the economy, a newspaper reported Monday.
	   Wee Cho Yaw, chairman of United Overseas Bank, told The Straits
Times that the current economic situation in the small island
