<SLUG> BC-SKorea-JP Morgan </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JP Morgan, Credit Suisse to help raise dlrs 2 billion loan for
</HEADLINE>
South Korea

<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ JP Morgan and Credit Suisse First
Boston have tentatively agreed to act as lead managers for a dlrs 2
billion loan South Korea's Export-Import Bank plans to introduce
this year, Seoul officials said Monday.
	   The deal is still in an early stage and details including
whether it will be a syndicate loan or bonds, when it will mature,
and how much interest it will carry have not been discussed yet,
South Korean bank officials said.
	   The South Korean government plans to use the money to help local
exporters and importers.
	   South Korea is anxious to attract foreign investment and loans
to revive its economy, which was bailed out by the International
Monetary Fund in December.
</TEXT>
