<HEADLINE>
Hundreds of thousands of honeybees block Transylvania highway
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ Hundreds of thousands of honeybees
blocked a national highway for a third day Monday after a truck
transporting 130 beehives overturned, a police officer said.
	   ``We had to reroute the traffic because the bees were attacking
the drivers, but we did not want to kill them,'' Lt. Rozalia
Slatean of the Satu Mare Police said by telephone.
	   The truck transporting the hives to a Transylvanian bee farm
overturned near the town of Decebal, 450 kilometers (281 miles)
northwest of Bucharest.
	   Slatean said bee farmer Ioan Bal is moving the damaged
honeycombs and the queen bees to new hives to lure the bees away
from the overturned truck.
	   Bal told police the accident resulted in lei 80 million (almost
dlrs 10,000) in damages. No one was injured.
</TEXT>
