</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with EU also freezing assets abroad; Kosovo Albanian
reaction. &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos &QL; 
 &UR; By ISMET HAJDARI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) _ As Europe banned investment in
Serbia and weighed other ways to halt violence in Kosovo, Serbs
reported fresh clashes in the secessionist province Monday and a
U.S. diplomat and ethnic Albanian leader toured a battle-torn area.
	   European Union foreign ministers, meeting in Luxembourg, banned
investment in Serbia and froze the country's assets abroad for ''a
campaign of violence going far beyond'' a legitimate strike against
