were only a ``small step'' compared to the situation on the ground.
	   ``NATO should become involved in Kosovo, because the Serbian
regime has had practice with sanctions and knows ways of bypassing
them,'' said Nekibe Kelmendi, head of the Albanians' largest party,
the Democratic League of Kosovo. ``It is a regime that only
respects the language of force.''
