<TEXT>
	   FIFA is counting the ballots in the Paris election for the new
president of the international soccer federation. There is no
indication how long the vote count will take, and a second ballot
may be needed if neither candidate received the two-thirds vote
(128 of 191) needed for a first-ballot win.
	   If a second ballot is needed, it will take place immediately
after the vote count is completed.
