<HEADLINE>
Russian police say diplomat's son died from drowning
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ An autopsy on the son of a North Korean diplomat
determined Monday that the toddler died from drowning, a news
agency said.
	   The 2-year-old disappeared May 30 during a picnic with his
father and other North Korean diplomats in a park in southwestern
Moscow.
	   His body was recovered Saturday from a small tributary to the
Moscow River about 2 kilometers (more than a mile) downstream from
where he disappeared.
	   Forensic tests conducted Monday confirmed that the toddler died
from drowning, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported, citing
unidentified police officials. Further tests will determine whether
he died in the same river where he was found.
	   Police tend to believe the death was an accident, but will wait
for final test results to reach a formal conclusion, the report
said.
