<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Barter Trade </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mahathir: Malaysia no longer concerned over fluctuations of
</HEADLINE>
ringgit &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Prime Minister Mahathir said
Malaysia was moving towards barter trade and no longer cares about
fluctuations in the value of the ringgit against the U.S. dollar, a
news report said Monday.
	   ``What we want to do is to get away from the value of the
ringgit and this can be done easily by conducting trade on a
counter trade or through practical bartering,'' Mahathir was quoted
by Bernama news as saying.
	   The ringgit has already lost about 40 percent of its value since
Southeast Asia plunged into economic turmoil last year.
	   ``We are not very concerned anymore,'' Mahathir said when asked
about the ringgit's further decline Monday morning below the 4
ringgit mark to 4.15 ringgit against the dollar.
	   Malaysia is expected to start conducting some trade through the
counter trade or barter system in an effort to reduce dependence on
foreign currencies, especially the U.S. dollar.
</TEXT>
