partner Germany following a financial crisis at home, but Boris
Yeltsin says he won't come begging for aid. GERMANY-YELTSIN.
Arrival scheduled for 1500 GMT.
	   FRANKFURT _ As workers using ultrasound equipment examined
wheels on Germany's original high-speed train fleet, rail officials
on Monday pledged openness to restore confidence shaken by the
catastrophic train accident that killed nearly 100 people.
