<HEADLINE>
BNP MP asks party workers to carry licensed arms during long march, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
BNP MP asks party workers to carry licensed arms during long march, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   BNP leader Lt Col (retd) Akbar Hossain MP today called upon the
leaders and workers of his party to carry licensed arms during the
June 9-10 long march.
	   Addressing a party rally here, Akbar warned that the government
will be held responsible if it attempt to create obstacle to the
long march.
	   Rabeya Bhuiyan who presided over the rally said that the ruling
party has decided to show white flag on the day of long march. ``It
is all right if the white flag is meant to welcome Begum Zia. But
they will resist if there is any evil design behind it.''
	   The rally was also addressed, among others, by Kamal Uddin
Chowdhury, Jahangir Ahmed, Shah Md Selim, Abdur Rouf Farooq.
	   It was followed by a procession that paraded the town drumming
up support for the long march.
	   
