	   The Surveillance Team of Securities and Exchange Commission
(SEC) has started on-line surveillance and monitoring of daily
trading of the Chittagong Stock Exchange (CSE) through the computer
terminal set up at the commission office, says a press release.
	   With the introduction of state-art-technology in the trading
system with CSE the Commission will from now on be able to monitor
the daily trading of those scripts currently being traded under the
automated trading system of CSE.
	   
