	   The 97th auction of the 90-Day Treasury Bill, the 88th auction
of the 30-Day and the 180-Day Treasury Bills and the 62nd auction
of the 1-year Treasury Bill were held on Sunday, says a Bangladesh
Bank press release.
	   Some 45 bids for a total of Tk 264.50 crore of 30-Day Bill, 7
bids for a total of Tk 30 crore of 90-Day Bill, two bids for a
total of Tk 5.50 crore of 180-Day Bill and 30 bids for a total of
Tk 147.59 crore of 1-Year Bill were offered.
	   Of these, 12 bids for a total of Tk 66 crore of 1-Year Bill were
accepted. The bids offered for the 90-Day and 180-Day and 1-Year
Bills were not accepted.
	   The weighted average prices of the accepted bids against 30-Day
ad 1-Year ills were Tk 99.31 and Tk 90.70 per 100 Taka
respectively. The corresponding yields are 8.36% and 10.25% per
annum.
	   
</TEXT>
