<HEADLINE>
CSE drops by 11.32 points, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
CSE drops by 11.32 points, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The All Securities Price Index at the Chittagong Stock Exchange
marked a fall on Monday after experiencing continued rise in last
few days.
	   The benchmark at the country's second bourse dropped by 11.32
points or 3.50 per cent to 312.05 points from Saturday's 323.37
points with losers outnumbering the gainers.
	   Shares of 43 listed securities were transacted, of which only
four gained, 37 incurred loss and two remained unchanged.
	   Some 304,615 shares and debentures valued at Tk 1.39 crore were
traded as against 143,002 shares worth Tk 99.55 lakh on the
previous day.
	   Chic Tex (123,500), Beximco Pharma (49,300), Quasem Drycells
(47,750), Shine Pukur (31,550) and Eagle Star (17,950) were among
the volume leaders.
	   Major losers included CTG Cement (-Tk 113.11), Apex Tannery (-Tk
53.55), Usmania Glass (-Tk 51.55), Meghna Cement (-Tk 46.79),
Olympic Industries (-Tk 41.58) and Square Pharma (-Tk 39.00).
	   There was no significant gainer of the day.
	   Market capitalisation stood at Tk 52.88 billion equivalent to US
dollar 1.13 billion.
	   
</TEXT>
