	   A DEFEATED candidate on Sunday launched a legal action to
challenge the result of the election in her functional
constituency.
	   Ann Chiang Lai-wan, who lost by just one vote to Tang Siu-tong
in the Regional Council constituency election on 24 May, has filed
a petition with the High Court seeking a new verdict on the outcome
of the poll.
	   Her lawyers are said to be solicitor Anna Wu Hung-yuk, a former
legislator, and barristers Gladys Li Chi-hei, former Bar
Association chairwoman, and Hector Poon.
	   The two defendants are Mr Tang and the returning officer of the
counting centre.
	   The controversy revolved around ballots marked with ticks
instead of numbers to indicate voter preference.
	   It is understood the returning officer deemed the votes valid.
	   
