<SLUG> ENCOMIUM-FOR-HASNAT'S sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Encomium for Hasnat's travelogue, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Encomium for Hasnat's travelogue, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The publication ceremony of eminent poet Hasnat Abdul Hai's
travelogue Andalusia's publication ceremony was held in the LGRD
auditorium at Agargaon in a festive mood last evening. State
Minister for Information Prof. Abu Sayeed attended the programme as
chief guest and poet Shamsur Rahman and Prof. Anisuzzaman were
special guests. Prof. Zillur Rahman Siddique presided over the
function. Sayed Manjurul Islam read the keynote paper on Andalusia.
The book is based on the writer's interesting experience while on a
tour of Spain.
	   Earlier a still photograph exhibition on Cordova, Granada,
Andalusia and Seville of Spain taken by Hasnat Abdul Hai was
inaugurated by Poet Shamsur Rahman.
	   In his paper, Sayeed Manjurul Islam said that many travelogues
had been written by many writers but the travelogue which had been
written with the writer's farsightedness and imagination had not
only earned recognition as travelogue but had also won acclaim as a
great piece of literary work. He said that Rabindranath Tagore at
the age of 17 visited Europe and wrote a travelogue on Europe which
became a great piece of literary work. Russia'r Chiti of Tagore had
also become very popular. Sayeed Manjurul Islam said that the
reason was Rabindranath not only wrote a simple travelogue; he
tried to depict the art, culture, history, literature and every
possible thing about a nation through his book.
	   He said the same thing could be said about Hasnat Abdul Hai's
Andalusia where the writer had not only expressed his feelings
about the historic city of Spain but had also depicted the art,
culture, history and literature of Spain through his creative mind
and natural ability. He said the success of this book lies there.
	   Professor Abu Sayed said the writer had described his tour of
Spain in his book with his great imaginative and creative mind. The
minister added that the important point about this book was he had
beautifully depicted the history, art, culture and literature of
Spain.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 THE INDEPENDENT all rights reserved as
distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
