<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Activist Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkish rights activist wounded in assassination attempt is
</HEADLINE>
released from hospital &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) _ A leading human rights activist who barely
survived an assassination attempt last month went home from the
hospital Monday.
	   Akin Birdal, 50, underwent two operations after being shot six
times on May 12. Doctors said it will take him from six weeks to
three months to fully recover.
	   Two men have confessed to shooting Birdal and were identified by
him. Police also arrested the alleged mastermind.
	   Birdal has won international respect for his opposition to
torture and the forced evacuation of Kurdish villages in
southeastern Turkey by the military in its war against Kurdish
guerrillas.
	   From his hospital bed, Birdal had vowed to continue his work.
``The assault has strengthened my belief in the values that we have
to fight for,'' he said.
	   (ht-cph)
