<HEADLINE>
CHT accord a great achievement of Hasina, says Lankan FM, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
CHT accord a great achievement of Hasina, says Lankan FM, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Visiting Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar
yesterday backed the peace accord on Chittagong Hill Tracts,
calling it ``a great and tremendous achievement of Sheikh Hasina.''
	   ``What Sheikh Hasina has done in Bangladesh won a great
admiration,'' he said addressing a workers' rally of ruling Awami
League at the historic Paltan Maidan, the same site from where
opposition BNP will begin its long march towards CHT on Tuesday.
	   The Lankan minister said she (Hasina) had succeeded when so many
failed in bringing peace in the region.
	   ``My sincere hope the peace that she has brought will continue
and be maintained,'' he said before concluding his speech saying
``Joy Bangla.''
	   About the two decades of insurgency in CHT, Kadirgamar said, we
in Sri Lanka have also the same problem...one group of people in my
country wants to secede for 25 years and that has caused a great
deal of bloodshed.
	   In this regard, he said, ``our President whose father and
husband have been assassinated is trying to negotiate the problem.
	   ``Everything should be negotiated in talks and discussion.''
	   The Lankan Foreign Minister termed Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur
Rahman, who was brutally killed, a great leader not only of
Bangladesh, but also of South Asia.
	   ``I am glad that his surviving daughter is now the Prime
Minister of your country,'' he said.
	   
