<HEADLINE>
Blair to meet with Kohl Tuesday to discuss EU summit agenda
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BONN, Germany (AP) _ British Prime Minister Tony Blair will meet
Tuesday with German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in Bonn to prepare for
this weekend's European Union summit in Cardiff, Wales.
	   Blair, winding up a tour of European capitals in his capacity as
EU president, is to discuss the summit's agenda with Kohl for about
90 minutes before traveling to Paris, his last stop, the British
Embassy in Bonn said.
	   Continent-wide efforts to fight unemployment, organized crime
and drugs are among items to be taken up at the summit, Blair's
last as EU president.
	   Austria takes over the presidency July 1.
