<HEADLINE>
One gets life for killing wife in Satkhira, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
One gets life for killing wife in Satkhira, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Md. Didar Ali Fakir, Additional District and Sessions Judge in a
judgement delivered here recently sentenced one person to life-term
imprisonment and fined Taka 2,000, in default, to suffer another
three months RI on charge of murdering his wife.
	   The judge also sentenced another person (brother of the killer)
to two years rigorous imprisonment and fined Taka 500 , in default,
to suffer another one month's RI.The prosecution story in brief is
that, the convict Adar Ali Gazi beat his wife Anwara Khatun over a
family dispute on March 13, 1987 killing her on the spot.
	   Later Adar Ali poured poison into her mouth to suppress the
murder and his brother Daud Gazi informed the thana police that
Anwara committed suicide by taking poision following a quarrel with
her family.A case was registered with the Sadar police in this
connection.The investigating officer submitted chargesheet against
the accused after an enquiry.
	   
