<HEADLINE>
Garment worker murdered, 3 others commit suicide in city, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Garment worker murdered, 3 others commit suicide in city, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   A garment worker was murdered and three people committed suicide
in separate incidents in the city during the last 24 hours.
	   Police said Mizanur Rahman Mizan (25), a garment worker, was
stabbed to death at the city's Pallabi area yesterday.
	   Witnesses said a gang of miscreants stabbed him indiscriminately
at about 1 pm, and fled the scene. He died on his way to hospital.
	   The body was sent to the Dhaka Medical College Hospital (DMCH)
for autopsy.
	   Abdul Wahab (25), allegedly committed suicide at his residence
at 14/1 Shajahanpur on Saturday night.
	   The motive behind the incident could not be ascertained
immediately, police said.
	   The body of Habibur Rahman Habib (40), a resident of 25/2 Lake
Circus, Kalabagan, was found hanging from the ceiling of the house
yesterday morning.
	   Police described it as a suicide. But, DMCH sources said the
body bore some injury marks.
	   The body of Manjur Rahman Manjur, a resident of 606 Ibrahimpur,
was recovered by the police last morning, which was found tied
against a tree with a shirt at the Suhrawardy Uddyan.
	   Police suspect it as a suicide. The body was sent to the DMCH
morgue.
	   Separate cases were filed with respective police stations in
this connections.
	   
</TEXT>
