<SLUG> ACCOMODATION-PROBLEM sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Accommodation problem hampers academic activities, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Accommodation problem hampers academic activities, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Academic activities of the university are being hampered for
lack of adequate number of classrooms and teachers' rooms. The
rooms in the university are small enough to make spaces for all the
students of a class. As a result, most classrooms remain crowded.
Many students attend the classes standing inside the rooms.
	   An estimate shows that the number of students under the Arts and
Social Science faculties is around 12,500. There are about 200
teachers in the 16 departments under the faculties. But there are
only 27 classrooms and 117 teachers' rooms which cannot cope with
the situation. Classes of three of the departments under the
faculties are held in the Business Studies building.
	   Yet another class is held at the building for Arts and Crafts
Department. Students of these two faculties usually gather at the
teacher's room and the teacher asks them where they want to hold
the class. The search for a free room then begins.Some of the
departments do not have their own classrooms. Students of such
departments move from one section of the main building to another,
looking for a place to hold the classes.
	   Some teachers take their classes during the breaks. Sometimes
classes are also held in the seminar room or even at the teacher's
room. The Computer Science Department has only one classroom. Lack
of accommodation pushes two or more teachers to sit in one room.
Muhammad Mizanuddin, a university teacher, said the accommodation
problem of the students and teachers could only be solved by
constructing a fourth building of the Arts Faculty.
	   
</TEXT>
