	   A DRIVER and his two passengers escaped injury on Sunday morning
when the car they were travelling in crashed into an electricity
meter box and caught fire.
	   Firemen arrived and using two foam spray jets put out the blaze
in about 10 minutes.
	   The driver, surnamed Yiu, 27, and the two passengers escaped
from the car before the blaze and were not injured.
	   Police said the crash at the junction of Prince Edward Road West
and Embankment Road happened about 4am.
	   Mr Yiu lost control of the car as he was turning into Embankment
Road and crashed through a two-metre railing before ramming into
the electricity meter box.
	   
