<HEADLINE>
Industrial Clinic at Rajghat lying unused, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Industrial Clinic at Rajghat lying unused, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Industrial Clinic at Rajghat Industrial Area under
Abhoynagar thana of the district has been lying inoperative for a
long time depriving at least 30,000 people of medicare facilities .
It may be mentioned that the Health Ministry and the Public Works
Ministry of the then government established a 110-bed Industrial
Clinic at Rajghat Industrial Area in 1982-83 fiscal year. Soon
after establishment of the clinic, the local Health Department
recruited two senior staff nurses and 14 officers and employees
temporarily as per verbal orders of the Health Ministry .
	   But the ENAM committee expressed its inability to sanction funds
against the project on the plea that there was no order for
increasing posts. As a result, the officers and employees of the
clinic were either transferred or adjusted elsewhere. The project
remained abandoned depriving the people of medicare facilities .
Meanwhile, valuable materials of the clinic have been stolen on
over a dozen occasions.
	   But the local administration all along remained indifferent for
mysterious reasons. Moreover, the clinic has turned into a den for
the criminals due to the negligence of the concerned authority .
The patriotic people have urged upon the competent authority to
take immediate steps to save the clinic from total destruction and
arrange for extending proper medicare facilities to the people of
the industrial area.One arrestedIdris Ali, a local leader of the
extremist group Sramajibi Mukti Andolon was arrested by Kotwali
police from Shyamnagar village in Sadar thana at noon on June 2.
	   Kotwali thana source said that acting on a tip-off the
Officer-in-Charge CA Halim along with SI Fazlur Rahman gheraoed a
garden of the village and arrested Idris Ali who was sleeping
there. The police added that Idris Ali was a local leader of the
armed extremist group Sramajibi Mukti Andolon. A few days ago one
of his gangmates was arrested by the Kotwali police with 57 rounds
of cartridges. At that time, Idris Ali managed to escape. There
were three cases against Idris Ali with Kotwali thana and many
cases with Kaligonj thana of Jhenidah district, it is learnt .
	   
</TEXT>
