MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The people of Faridpur town have demanded shifting of the morgue
to the Faridpur Medical College Hospital from its present site. The
lone morgue in the district situated on the northern side of
Faridpur General Hospital was set up during the British rule.
	   The morgue has become dilapidated now. Besides, it is too small
to conduct autopsy of two bodies at a time. The surrounding areas
of the morgue have become thickly populated. The atmosphere in the
surrounding areas of the morgue becomes polluted very often when
rotten and decomposed bodies are kept there for autopsy. Moreover,
people living in the neighbourhood suffer from psychological
problems.
	   When the attention of the Civil Surgeon Abul Hossain was drawn
to the matter, he opined that a morgue should be situated on the
premises of a medical college, if there be any. So, the morgue
should be shifted to Faridpur Medical College Hospital premises
from its present site and housed in a suitable spacious building to
cope with the changing situation.
	   
</TEXT>
