<HEADLINE>
Power consumers suffer in Kishoreganj, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Power consumers suffer in Kishoreganj, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The electricity consumers under Bajitpur-Kuliarchar feeder line
have been suffering due to severe loadshedding.Acute power crisis
has made the life of the people miserable. Meanwhile the consumers
have taken to the streets demanding uninterrupted power supply.
	   The consumers, numbering more than 10,000 under
Bajitpur-Kuliarchar feeder line of the Power Development Board
(PDB) and Rural Electrification Board (REB) have been suffering due
to severe loadshedding for the last two years. Consumers complain
that 18/20 hours loadshedding everyday has become a common feature
in their daily life.
	   Sources say that power crisis became acute when the 5th unit of
150 megawatt at Ashuganj Power Plant was closed down for repair.
The repair work was supposed to be completed in three days. But it
has not been completed even after 12 days , according to informed
sources.
	   The sources added that repair of the Bhairab-Kuliarchar 33 kv
electricity line costing Taka 5 lakh was not completed even after
one year.Patients in hospitals and thana health complexes and
students , particularly the HSC examinees are the worst sufferers.
	   
</TEXT>
