<HEADLINE>
Council review `not tied to market row', HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
Council review `not tied to market row', HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
   Susan LanninASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE government has denied any link between an order for the
Provisional Urban Council to vacate Central Market and a review of
district organisations.
	   The government plans to move the market from Queen's Road to
Hollywood Road and turn the area into a bus terminal and commercial
building.
	   But PUC members want the market to stay put and the site
redeveloped to include recreational and cultural facilities.
	   Chairman of the PUC working group on the issue, Democrat Kam
Nai-wai, said members would investigate the rights of the council
in relation to land owned by the government. ``We want to know if
the government has the right to take over the site.'' He said the
group would discuss the resumption order on Monday.
	   A spokesman for the Planning, Environment and Lands Bureau said
despite six years of discussion with councillors, little had been
achieved, and the need for a bus terminus on the site was
``urgent''.
	   A government statement said: ``We cannot afford to wait until
PUC acceptance or otherwise of our offer to reprovision the market
before we make preparations for the redevelopment of the Central
Market site.'' It said redevelopment of the market and the review
of the municipal councils were separate issues.
	   But Urban Councillor Jennifer Chow Kit-bung, said the move was
an attack on the council's power.
	   ``The Urban Council has much power and the Government thinks
it's time to review its duties and responsibilities.'' Copyright
1998 HONGKONG STANDARD all rights reserved as distributed by
WorldSources, Inc. 	   
</TEXT>
