<HEADLINE>
Air Macau to lease Airbus to Portugal, HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
Air Macau to lease Airbus to Portugal, HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
   Harald BruningASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   AIR Macau will lease one of its three Airbus A-320s to
Portugal's national airline, TAP-Air Portugal, a spokesman for Air
Macau said on Sunday.
	   The spokesman said the lease agreement had been concluded
following two weeks of negotiations between the two airlines.
	   The lease included the aircraft's crew, the spokesman said,
adding the Air Macau plane was scheduled to leave for Lisbon in the
third week of June.
	   The Airbus is to remain with TAP-air Portugal for at least six
months.
	   The spokesman said TAP-Air Portugal would use the Airbus to meet
rising demand in Europe, at a time when air traffic in Asia is
expected to decrease further because of the region's current
financial crisis.
	   Air Macau has a fleet of seven Airbuses. The airline, which
started commercial operations in November 1995, flies to cities in
China, Taiwan, Thailand and the Philippines.
	   TAP-Air Portugal has a 25 per cent stake in Air Macau. China
National Aviation Corporation holds a 51 per cent stake in Air
Macau. Other shareholders include the Macau government and Stanley
Ho Hung-sun's STDM.
	   
</TEXT>
