<SLUG> FISH-NOT-VIAGRA sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fish not Viagra, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Fish not Viagra, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   A UAE national who has fathered 46 children has advised his
fellow countrymen to eat fish instead of taking Viagra (for
reinforcing virility). The story of this highly fecund male and his
prescription for attaining his level of fertility was reported by
Reuters quoting the daily Emirates News. The 48-year-old UAE
national, Ahmed Rashid bin Abaud, said he has sired 23 sons and 23
daughters by eight wives and that one of these eight wives has
given birth to 17 children. His slogan is Eat fish and more fish'.
	   Five of his wives have been divorced and the remaining three
live with him. As four wives at a time is permissible, Abaud has
place for one more which, hopefully, will soon be filled. The
habitual bridegroom is looking for a teenager not only to become
his latest consort but also to bear children leading to further
augmentation in the number of his offspring. May this fish eater's
family increase further and further.
	   What wonders fish can do!From this it is possible to deduce that
in an overpopulated country like ours fish cannot be the ideal
food. But fish has been our natural food, eaten from traditional
habit rather than from the compulsion of enhancing potency. If fish
is an aphrodisiac, that is an added benefit, hitherto unrecognised.
Bengalis need no encouragement to eat fish which is their favourite
food. But in view of the newly revealed magical properties of fish,
the slogan in their case should be ``Eat fish but not without
contraception.''
	   
</TEXT>
