<HEADLINE>
Dallas Stars' Zubov arrested, accused of assaulting wife
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   COPPELL, Texas (AP) _ Dallas Stars defenseman Sergei Zubov has
been arrested on charges of assaulting his wife and brandishing a
knife.
	   Zubov, 27, was charged with aggravated assault and family
violence, a second-degree felony.
	   Coppell police said they went to Zubov's house shortly after 3
a.m. (0700 GMT) Sunday after someone at the home called police and
hung up.
	   Officers, who determined that Zubov had exhibited a kitchen
knife in the alleged assault, took him into custody, Coppell police
Capt. Wade Goolsby said. He said the weapon was recovered.
	   Zubov's wife, Irina, was not believed to have been injured.
	   Zubov, who was the Stars' second-leading scorer during the
playoffs with nine points in 16 games, was released Sunday on dlrs
5,000 bond set by Municipal Judge Kim Nesbitt.
	   ``The Dallas Stars and the National Hockey League are
cooperating fully with the authorities and are offering our
assistance and support to both Sergei and Irina,'' Stars general
manager Bob Gainey said in a statement.
	   The club had no further comment. 	   
