<HEADLINE>
Sporting Lisbon signs Croatian coach Mirko Jozic
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LISBON, Portugal (AP) _ Sporting Lisbon announced Monday that it
had signed Croatian coach Mirko Jozic on a one-year contract.
	   Jozic, 58, replaces Carlos Manuel who quit last month after the
club finished the Portuguese first division in fourth place, 21
points behind champion FC Porto, on a 15-11-8 record. Manuel was
the club's fourth coach of the season.
	   Sporting has not won the league title for 16 years.
	   Jozic, who last week left Argentinean club Newell's Old Boys
after six months as coach, signed Sunday in Rome.
	   He led Colo Colo to the Chilean title in 1991, 1992 and 1994,
and coached Croatia's Hadjuk Split in 1996.
