	   KUALA LUMPUR, Sun. - The nation's biggest walking event, the
Malay Mail Big Walk 1998, was officially launched today by Datuk
Bandar Tan Sri Kamaruzzaman Shariff at Menara Kuala Lumpur.
	   This will be the 38th big walk organised by the Malay Mail.
Nearly 1,000 people turned up today to register for the event.
	   While queuing up to register, they listened to a talk given by
former national champion Khoo Chong Beng on ``The Art of Walking''.
	   In his opening speech, Kamaruzzaman said the 38th Malay Mail Big
Walk, more affectionately known as the ``Biggie'', would be an
excellent way to further nurture the spirit of healthy and clean
living among city dwellers.
	   Also present was the walk's organising chairman, Malay Mail
editor Fauzi Omar who said that with the walk taking place just 18
days before the Commonwealth Games, he hoped the turnout would
exceed the usual figure of 10,000 participants.
	   ``We have written to all 68 countries inviting their athletes to
participate,'' he said.
	   The walk will be held on Aug 23 at Padang Merbuk. It is jointly
organised by the Malay Mail, Kuala Lumpur City Hall, Malaysia
Tourism Promotion Board and the Federal Territory Amateur Athletic
Association.
	   Sponsors of the walk are Milo and Isomax with Menara Kuala
Lumpur being the venue sponsor and Time Highway Radio the official
radio station.
	   
</TEXT>
