<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1190 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Numerous showers and isolated thunderstorms developed over the
coastal waters of Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands this
morning. Most of the showers remained over the coastal waters, but
a few moved onshore over the U.S. Virgin Islands and the east coast
of Puerto Rico.
	   The heaviest rain fell just off the southeast coast of Puerto
Rico from Maunabo to Guayama.
	   The showers developed early this morning as an upper level area
of high pressure over the southeast Caribbean weakened, allowing an
upper trough to drift close to the islands.
	   Scattered showers are expected over the east half of Puerto Rico
and the U.S. Virgin islands this morning.
	   However, as sea breezes develop most of the shower activity is
expected to be pushed into the interior and western sections of
Puerto Rico by the afternoon.
	   A tropical wave located in the middle and upper levels of the
atmosphere passed over the Windward Islands overnight. This wave
will pass south of the local area today and is not expected to have
a direct effect on the local weather.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variably cloudy in the east with scattered morning
showers, becoming partly cloudy by afternoon. Partly cloudy in the
west this morning, becoming mostly cloudy in the afternoon with
scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind
east 10 to 20 mph except northeast along the coast. Chance of rain
is 50 percent.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with widely scattered
showers and skies becoming fair in the west. Low 70 to 80. Light
wind in the east. Chance of rain is 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with scattered showers. High around 90.
Wind east at 10 to 20 mph, except northeast along the coast. Chance
of rain is 40 percent.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly cloudy morning with showers likely, becoming
partly cloudy by afternoon. High around 75 in the mountains, 85 to
90 on the coasts. Wind east at 10 to 15 mph. Chance of rain is 60
percent.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with scattered showers. Slight chance
of a coastal thunderstorm. Low around 65 mountains, 75 to 80 on the
coasts. East wind 5 to 10 mph. Chance of rain is 30 percent.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with scattered showers. High around 75
in the mountains, 85 to 90 on the coasts. Wind east at 10 to 15
mph. Chance of rain is 30 percent.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variably cloudy in the east with scattered morning
showers, becoming partly sunny by afternoon. Partly cloudy west,
becoming mostly cloudy by afternoon with scattered showers and
isolated thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Southeast wind 10 to 15 mph.
Chance of rain is 40 percent.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with widely scattered
showers. Fair skies in the west. Low around 65 in the interior, 75
to 80 on the coasts. Light east wind. Chance of rain is 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with scattered showers and isolated
afternoon thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Southeast wind 10 to 15
mph. Chance of rain is 30 percent.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly sunny in the morning, becoming mostly cloudy in
the afternoon with scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms.
High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 20 mph except for an afternoon sea
breeze along the west coast. Chance of rain is 50 percent.
	   Tonight... Decreasing clouds with showers ending. Skies becoming
fair by midnight. Low 65 to 75. Light east wind. Chance of rain is
less than 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Mostly sunny in the morning, becoming variably cloudy
in the afternoon with scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms.
High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 20 mph except for an afternoon sea
breeze along the west coast. Chance of rain is 40 percent.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly sunny in the morning, becoming mostly cloudy by
afternoon with showers likely. Isolated thunderstorms in the west.
High around 75 on mountain peaks, 85 to 90 in lower valleys. East
wind 10 to 20 mph. Chance of rain is 60 percent.
	   Tonight... Decreasing clouds with showers ending before
midnight, becoming partly cloudy in the east with isolated showers.
Fair skies in the west. Low 65 to 75. East wind around 10 mph.
Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy morning, becoming variably cloudy in
the afternoon with scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High
around 75 on mountain peaks, 85 to 90 in lower valleys. Wind east
10 to 20 mph. Chance of rain is 40 percent.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Mostly cloudy in the morning with showers likely.
Isolated thunderstorms; becoming partly sunny by afternoon. High 90
to 95. Wind east at 10 to 15 mph and gusty. Chance of rain is 60
percent.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with widely scattered showers. Low 70
to 80. Wind east at 5 to 10 mph. Chance of rain is 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy and breezy with a 30 percent chance of
showers. High 80 to 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   This afternoon... Wind east to northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to
4 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east to northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft. Scattered
showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   This afternoon... Wind east to northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 2 to
4 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east to northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft. Scattered
showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Wind east to northeast 10 to 20 kt, except
variable less than 10 kt along the coast. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Scattered
showers. Widely scattered thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind variable, mainly east to northeast at 5 to 15
kt. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Isolated showers.
	   Tuesday... Wind east at 10 to 20 kt, except variable less than
10 kt along the coast. Seas 2 to 4 ft. Scattered showers and
isolated thunderstorms in the afternoon.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Tuesday night through Friday... A high pressure ridge will
continue across the subtropical Atlantic from the east central
Atlantic to the Bahamas. Wind east at 20 kt or less. Seas 5 ft or
less.
</TEXT>
