<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Boris Becker </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Boris Becker wavering on Wimbledon start
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HALLE, Germany (AP) _ Boris Becker said Monday he might play
Wimbledon this year after all, just one week after saying the
opposite.
	   Becker told reporters that his decision to enter the All-England
Championships depended on how well he played at this week's Halle
tournament, a grass tuneup for Wimbledon.
	   ``On Friday, I will announce whether I play Wimbledon '98 or
not,'' said Becker.
	   Becker has until Monday to accept a wild card for the grand slam
where he enjoyed his greatest career success with three singles
titles and six finals between 1985 and 1991.
	   Becker reached the semifinals at Halle last year, then was
ousted by Pete Sampras at Wimbledon. Afterwards, the former world
No. 1 said his 14th appearance was his last.
	   Since then Becker, who now only occasionally plays tournaments
and has moved into developing young German talent, has changed his
mind several times.
	    &UR; (rk)	   
</TEXT>
