</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UN-Drug Goals,0258 </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   UNITED NATIONS (AP) _ Here are the major themes and goals of the
UN special session on drugs which began Monday:
	   Precursor Chemicals: Set a target date of 2008 for controls on
``precursors'' _ legal chemicals which can be synthesized into
narcotics
	    &UR; ____ &QC; 
	   Amphetamines: With an estimated 30 million users worldwide,
amphetamines are the most widely abused synthetic drugs. The
session will approve a target date of 2003 for governments to
develop plans for curbing amphetamines with 2008 as the target for
a significant reduction in the manufacture, trafficking and abuse
of amphetamines.
	    &UR; ____ &QC; 
	   Judicial Cooperation: Sets 2003 as the target for governments to
take measures to improve judicial cooperation through such steps as
mutual legal assistance, streamlined extradition procedures and
seizure by air and on the seas.
	    &UR; ____ &QC; 
	   Money-laundering: Member states will be called on to reaffirm
their commitment to the 1988 convention on money-laundering
including seizure and confiscation of proceeds from the drug trade
and set 2003 as the target date for enabling national legislation.
	    &UR; ____ &QC; 
	   Drug demand: Sets 2008 as the target for national programs to
reduce demand through education and expanded treatment.
	    &UR; ____ &QC; 
	   Elimination of illcit crops: Establishes 2008 as the target for
a significant reduction in the illegal cultivation of opium
poppies, cannabis and cocoa through strengthened law enforcement,
eradication and offering farmers alternative crops.
</TEXT>
