	   PENANG, Fri. - The Tanjung Umno Youth has reiterated its call
for the resignation of the Penang Island Municipal Council
president Dr Teng Hock Nan.
	   The call was made today by its deputy chief Jalaluddin Md Ismail
in a Press statement.
	   This was despite the apology tendered by its head Raja Munir
Raja Mustapha Shah last month.
	   Jalaluddin said the apology to Dr Teng was Raja Munir's personal
action which had nothing to do with the Tanjung Umno Youth's stand.
	   ``We still want to have Dr Teng replaced as the council
president,'' he said, adding that it had recently passed a
no-confidence motion on the State Umno Youth deputy chief Mohamad
Ismail Mohd Othman on the issue of apology.
	   ``The matter has been raised to the State Youth leader Dr Abdul
Rahim Md Ghouse and national Youth chief Datuk Ahmad Zahid
Hamidi.''
	   Meanwhile, Raja Munir denied a Press report that he had
apologised to Dr Teng for his remarks on the council president.
	   He told the New Straits Times he had never apologised for making
the call for Dr Teng's resignation.
	   Raja Munir, a councillor, had last month caused a political
uproar when he said Dr Teng had been treating fellow councillors as
mere ``rubber stamps'' in major decision-making matters.
	   
</TEXT>
