<SLUG> CONTRACTOR-FINED sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Contractor fined RM40,000 for open burning, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Contractor fined RM40,000 for open burning, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - The Ampang Sessions Court today fined a
contractor RM40,000 for carrying out open burning at a garbage dump
in Kajang.
	   PortPower (M) Sdn Bhd admitted burning the garbage at the dump
site about 4.30pm on April 9.
	   The company, situated at Jalan Melor Satu, Taman Sri Ramal,
Kajang, was represented by its directors Mohd Fadzil Mohd Said and
Hamzah Abdul Hamid, both 34.
	   It is responsible for supervising the disposal of garbage at the
Kajang Municipal Council garbage dumping site at Kampung Sungai
Kembong, Semenyih.
	   An officer from the Department of Environment and a technician
had discovered the open burning when checking the site.
	   The company was charged under Section 22(1) of the Environmental
Quality Act 1974 which carries a maximum fine of RM100,000 or five
year's jail or both.
	   In mitigation, counsel Mohd Bashir Abd Kadir, for PortPower,
said the incident was caused by a third party.
	   He said the company had spent about RM7,000 to spread sand over
the affected area and that it had pleaded guilty to save the
court's time.
	   The company, he said, had, in the interest of the public,
stationed a guard at the dump site.
	   Wan Abdul Latiff Wan Jaafar and Abdul Malik Ahmad prosecuted
before judge Hue Siew Kheng. PortPower paid the fine.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
