<SLUG> SUSPENSION-OF-DAP sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`Suspension of DAP leaders indicates nepotism', NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
`Suspension of DAP leaders indicates nepotism', NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETALING JAYA, Fri. - Prime Minister Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir
Mohamad said today the suspension of two key DAP leaders and the
removal of another from their party positions, was an indication
that secretary-general Lim Kit Siang practices nepotism.
	   ``It looks likes Kit Siang is not concerned about his party. He
is more concerned about his son (MP for Kota Melaka Lim Guan Eng)
and his family.
	   This is actually, nepotism.
	   ``He chose his son as deputy secretary-general of the party. If
others do the same thing, he will call it nepotism.
	   ``DAP has not even formed the Government and he has already
given a place to his son. If DAP manages to form the Government one
day, his son, his wife and other family members will be in the
Cabinet,'' he said on his arrival at the Sultan Abdul Aziz Shah
International Airport in Subang after a working visit to Japan.
	   On Wednesday, the DAP central executive committee suspended its
vice- chairman Liew Ah Kim and treasurer Fung Ket Wing for
criticising its leadership at party meetings.
	   National publicity secretary Wee Choo Keong was relieved of his
position.
	   Asked to comment on the action against the three, Dr Mahathir
said: ``The fact that Kit Siang had brought his son to contest in a
constituency which he himself used to contest (Kota Melaka),
already reveals elements of nepotism and cronyism.''
	   
</TEXT>
