<HEADLINE>
Games just one short of full participation, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Games just one short of full participation, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - Youth and Sports Minister Tan Sri Muhyiddin
Yassin announced today that the Kuala Lumpur 1998 Commonwealth
Games is one country short of full participation - Tuvalu.
	   The last Games in Victoria, Canada in 1994 attracted 63
countries.
	   There are 69 member countries in the Commonwealth and St Helena
was the 68th country to confirm participation in the Kuala Lumpur
Games set for between Sept 11 and 21.
	   St Helena, which did not take part in the three previous Games,
confirmed participation earlier this week, and will send three
athletes and two officials.
	   ``I've asked Tan Sri Hashim Ali to invite two persons from
Tuvalu for the Games,'' said Muhyiddin at a briefing for newspaper
editors at his office.
	   Jen (R) Hashim is the executive chairman of Sukom Ninety Eight
Bhd, the organisers of the KL Games.
	   Sukom officials said this will be the first time that Tuvalu,
formerly called Ellice Islands, will participate in the Games if
they accept the invitation.
	   
</TEXT>
