	   THE Royal College of Physicians, Ireland Faculty of Occupational
Medicine held an admission ceremony for successful candidates who
sat for its Licentiate of Membership examination last Saturday at
Hospital Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia.
	   The event was hosted by Irish ambassador Brendon Lyons and wife
Mary at their residence in Jalan Ampang Hilir, Kuala Lumpur.
	   Present were Royal College of Physicians (Ireland) Faculty of
Occupational Medicine dean Dr Christopher Dick, its chief examiner
Dr David Courtney and wife Ruth, Malaysian Medical Association
president elect Dr P. Krishnan and wife Dr K. Saramma and
Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia Medical Faculty (Department of
Community Health) associate professor Dr K.G. Rampal.
	   Associates Sdn Bhd occupational physician Dr Ravindran R. Naidu,
Klinik Manalan occupational physician Dr S.R. Manalan, Overseas
Committee (Faculty of Occupational Medicine) of Royal College of
Physician member Dr S. Usha Rani, Allied Occupational Health and
Medical Services (Klinik H.M.S) occupational health physician Dr
Arup Pramanik, Institute of Respiratory Medicine Kuala Lumpur
Hospital head Dr I. Kuppusamy, Poliklinik Sumi occupational
physician Dr S. Vigneswaran were also there.
	   
