<HEADLINE>
Carry it in style, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Carry it in style, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   WHAT used to be an alternative to the pocket has now become a
necessary accessory for all women to have and to hold.
	   We're talking handbags here. For most women, the practical
shoulder bag that marries form and function is the perfect daytime
carrier.
	   But for night, pretty pouches and chic cases are the sacks that
would put you seriously in style.
	   To quote Domenico Dolce of Dolce &AMP; Gabbana: ``The handbag a
woman uses for a special occasion should be as extraordinary as a
Victorian jewel...
	   and just as glamorous.''
	   Beaded or embroidered, ornate evening bags are indeed
one-of-a-kind. And when it comes to tapestry, the craze for
Chinoiserie needlework is still in. So are beaded purses which are
said to have been at the fingertips of glamorous ladies since the
late 1700s - more than 200 years ago! But if you don't want its
rich finishes to compete with your dress, carry a simple one then.
	   Minimalistic chic carriers, such as the square silver mesh with
metal handle from Isetan or the beige satin envelope clutch from
Metrojaya, would easily go hand-in-hand with whatever you wear.
	   On the other hand, if you prefer a carrier with character, there
are quirky and kooky ones to choose from like Metrojaya's hatbox
holder, Prada's velvet onion bag or Nina Ricci's multi-coloured
goatskin drum case.
	   Some, such as Judith Leiber's odd-shaped collectible containers
have been spotted on several jet-setting socialites and celebrities
who wear them as chunky necklaces! What a conversation piece. Get a
grip. Case closed.
	   
</TEXT>
