<SLUG> BC-Britain-BBC Americas </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BBC veteran to head Americas operations
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The British Broadcasting Corp. said Monday it had
appointed a veteran executive, Peter Phippen, as president and
chief executive of its growing BBC Worldwide Americas subsidiary.
	   Phippen had previously been managing director of BBC Worldwide's
British region.
	   Phippen will run BBC activities including the entertainment
channel BBC America, as well as various co-production and licensing
arrangements with broadcasters in the Americas and a partnership
with the television group Discovery in South America.
	   ``I'm excited and somewhat awed by the size of the opportunity
in the Americas,'' said Phippen, who will be based in New York.
``But the time is right to seize it.''
	   Phippen's old post goes to Peter Teague, who has been serving as
acting chief executive of BBC Worldwide, the commercial division of
the publicly-funded broadcaster. Teague will also become deputy
chief executive of BBC Worldwide.
	   (db)
</TEXT>
