<HEADLINE>
Uzbekistan seeking loans from Asian bank
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Uzbekistan is negotiating a dlrs 50 million loan
from the Asian Development Bank to promote small- and medium-sized
businesses, the Interfax news agency said.
	   Uzbekistan hopes to receive and disburse the funds in early
1999, said Rustam Azimov, head of the Uzbek National Bank for
Foreign Economic Activity in the Central Asian country.
