<HEADLINE>
U.S. Coast Guard repatriates seven Cuban migrants
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) _ The U.S. Coast Guard repatriated
seven Cubans rescued last week from a 15-foot boat near the
Bahamas, officials said Monday.
	   They were taken to the port at Bahia de Cabanas, Cuba Saturday
morning. An eighth migrant was granted political asylum and sent to
the U.S. Navy Base at Guantanamo Bay, Cuba, to begin applying for a
visa.
	   The eight Cubans were found adrift June 2 about 30 miles
southeast of Cay Lobos in the Bahamas. The boat's engine had
failed, the Coast Guard said.
