	   KLUANG, Fri. - About 3,000 Hindu devotees are expected to throng
the Sri Maha Mariamman temple in Jalan Hospital here to mark the
two-day Vaigasi Visagam festival celebrations starting tomorrow.
	   The annual festival will begin at 6pm with the abishega poojas
followed by the special poojas held in conjunction with the Yang
di-Pertuan Agong's birthday celebrations.
	   On Sunday at 6am there will be a kavadi procession from Jalan
Omar to the temple in Jalan Hospital. A vegetarian lunch will also
be held at noon.
	   In the evening, a procession with Goddess Amman will be held in
the temple.
	   
