	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - There appears to be a Coca-Cola price war
in the Klang Valley as several supermarkets have lowered prices
since the last Wise Spending price check.
	   Aktif Lifestyle supermarket at the Mall has reduced the price to
RM1.25 per 1.5 litre bottle, Uda Ocean was selling the item at
RM1.95 while TMC reduced the price to RM2.29 from RM2.40 per
bottle.
	   Some supermarkets also increased the prices of certain items
slightly.
	   As an example, Carrefour was selling Clorox bleach at a higher
price of RM2.65 compared to RM2.15 per litre on May 29.
	   Meanwhile, Jusco One Utama has increased the price of the item
by 20 sen, offering it for RM2.85 per litre.
	   Prices of other items remained relatively stable.
	   In Ipoh, the prices of several items at supermarkets in the city
remained unchanged since early this week, though the prices of some
items recorded an increase.
	   For example, a 700ml Organics shampoo was selling for RM17.80 at
Super Kinta, but at Jaya Jusco the price was RM21.95. This was much
higher than the previous price of RM17.90 during the supermarket's
`Ma'al Hijrah' sale earlier this week.
	   Another item is the Kleenex brand tissue which was selling for
RM5.50 at Jaya Jusco compared to its earlier price of RM5, while
the price of Scottex toilet rolls at Super Kinta went down from
RM6.50 to RM4.50.
	   Super Kinta was also selling Clorox bleach at a cheaper price of
RM2.60 compared with its earlier price of RM3.30.
	   In Johor Baru, there was slight variation in prices of most
items at the different supermarkets.
	   However there was an exception for 700ml Organics shampoo priced
at RM19.05, which was RM3.40 more at Tops, compared to Pasaraya
Coop.
	   In Penang, prices of Organics shampoo 700ml remained the same
between RM16.35 and RM18.50 at the two shopping complexes.
	   Colgate toothpaste 250g was still unavailable at the Looking
Good while it was selling RM5.50 at the Super Komtar.
	   
</TEXT>
