<HEADLINE>
Reduced entrance charges to KL Tower, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Reduced entrance charges to KL Tower, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MENARA Kuala Lumpur has come up with a family package for
visitors with children aged between four and 12 - charging only RM3
for admission to the observation platform instead of the usual RM8.
	   In addition, the families will receive various gifts including a
McDonalds meal discount voucher.
	   The first 100 families to visit the tower during the week will
stand to receive special gifts from KL Tower and Pureen.
	   Menara Kuala Lumpur Sdn Bhd chief executive officer Shahidah
Ridwan said the Family Week is from June 7 to 14.
	   The package was introduced as a tribute to mothers (Mother's Day
- May 10), fathers (Father's Day - June 21) and children
(Children's Day - Nov 20).
	   ``Through these promotional events, our aim is to ensure that
all visitors enjoy their visits and come back again to join our
other fun and educational programmes held throughout the year,''
she said.
	   The Family Week at Menara Kuala Lumpur and Happy Family package
were launched by Youth and Sports Ministry Parliamentary Secretary
Datuk Shahrizat Jalil on June 4.
	   Shahidah said several family-oriented contests will be held with
the grand finals to take place on June 14.
	   She said the contests include ``Mummy I Love You'' poem-reading
contest in Bahasa Malaysia in which children aged between seven and
12 can dedicate poems to their mothers.
	   Others were the ``Parent Child Look-A-Like'' contest in which
only 10 families will be selected to enter the final and the
``You're My Cutest Baby'' contest with 15 babies below two eligible
for the final.
	   ``Winners of the contests will receive attractive prizes
including hampers from KL Tower and Pureen worth between RM50 and
RM300 as well as three vouchers each for lunch, high tea and dinner
from the Seri Angkasa Revolving Restaurant,'' she said.
	   She said entry forms can be obtained from newspapers and should
be sent to Pertandingan Minggu Keluarga Menara Kuala Lumpur '98,
c/o Bahagian Pemasaran dan Perhubungan, Menara Kuala Lumpur Sdn
Bhd, 188533-A, Jalan Punchak, off Jalan P. Ramlee, 50250 Kuala
Lumpur by June 10.
	   Shahidah said 25 per cent discount on tickets will be given for
two adults with four or more children.
	   Those purchasing a minimum of 10 tickets for adults and children
will get a child's ticket free.
	   ``Apart from that, they can also enjoy a 50 per cent discount on
McDonalds Tower Burger with every purchase of two large McValue
meals,''
	   she said.
	   
</TEXT>
