	   LOVE and care is important when looking after the sick and
elderly. This is what the College of Nursing in Klang is strongly
stressing to its student nurses.
	   To instill the caring concept in them, the college organised a
one-day seminar for some 80 student nurses at its premises in Jalan
Istana, Klang on Wednesday.
	   Specialists in the field of gerontology presented a few papers
on the topic and stressed the need for love and care when caring
for the elderly and the sick when they are warded in hospitals.
	   The seminar was one of the activities held by the College of
Nursing in conjunction with the recent Nurses Day celebration.
	   Eighty-seven staff members and student nurses donated blood to
the Tengku Ampuan Rahimah's hospital blood bank recently.
	   For some of the student nurses, it was a new experience but they
took it in good spirit as they felt that such a contribution was
another way of showing that they cared for those in need.
	   Tengku Ampuan Rahimah Hospital deputy director Dr N.K.S.
Sathiaseelan, who was present at the blood donation drive, said the
student nurses and staff of the college were sporting as they did
not hesitate when told that they was an appeal to donate blood to
the hospital blood bank.
	   
