	   SEVENTY-seven children from Asrama Damai, Kuang, Selangor were
treated to a fun field day at Zoo Negara recently as they
participated in activities organised by the Arab-Malaysian Group.
	   The children, aged between five and 17, were put in groups of
not more than nine each.
	   They had lots of fun during the walkabout where the children
were asked questions about the animals and plants at the zoo.
	   Each group was awarded points for correct answers and were later
given prizes.
	   Before the activities, Arab-Malaysian Merchant Bank Berhad
general manager Fauziah Yacob said despite the busy schedule, the
organisation had not forgotten to lend a helping hand to the less
fortunate.
	   ``We have always helped the elderly, orphaned, abused children
and the handicapped. We normally give donations in cash, or
sometimes in kind,''
	   she said.
	   Fauziah said the group had chosen Asrama Damai after a community
service project in December.
	   She said during the project, they got to know the home and
decided to help the orphaned children there.
	   Also on the itinerary that day was a three-legged race and
``wrapping the mummy'' contest.
	   The children were enthusiastic and happy to participate in the
competition and win prizes.
	   After the games, the children enjoyed lunch at the Kentucky
Fried Chicken outlet.
	   
