	   THE Malacca Big Bikers' Association organised its first joint
cavalcade with the Pan Pacific Legacy Hotel from the hotel premises
in Jalan Hang Tuah, Malacca, to the Mahkota Parade complex in Jalan
Merdeka.
	   Eighteen bikers clad in macho leather jackets and riding garb
escorted hotel staff who rode in two Eleksuria, the electric car
manufactured by Perusahaan Otomobil Elektrik Malaysia.
	   Passing through Jonker's Street and the historical complex in
Jalan Laksamana, the entourage of Harley Davidsons, Hondas and
Yamaha Viragos were cheered as they went along these routes.
	   Association secretary Norman Abdul Rahman said apart from
holding programmes to boost fellowship among bikers, MBBA organised
trips to old folk's homes.
	   ``We also hope to participate more actively in tourism-related
events to attract tourists to our State,'' he said.
	   Hotel marketing communications manager Sherry Lee Ming Ming said
the cavalcade was to promote Malacca for the Commonwealth Games.
	   
