<HEADLINE>
Chase to Acquire Global Custody from Morgan Stanley, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
Chase to Acquire Global Custody from Morgan Stanley, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Chase Manhattan Corp. and Morgan Stanley Dean Witter &AMP; Co.
recently announced that they have reached a definitive agreement
under which Chase will acquire global custody business of Morgan
Stanley Dean Witter. Terms of the purchase, which is expected to be
completed later this year, were not disclosed.
	   The two Morgan Stanley entries involved in the agreement --
Morgan Stanley Trust Co. and Morgan Stanley Bank Luxembourg, S.A.
-- have more than $400 billion of assets under custody. The clients
and staff joining Chase will be integrated gradually into Chase
Global Investor Services, the bank's worldwide securities trust and
custody Business.
	   James Zeigon, head of Chase Global Services, which includes
Global Investor Services, said, ''This acquisition will strengthen
Chase's leading position in the custody business and further
underscores the bank's commitment to remaining the pre-eminent
provider in the industry.'' The addition of the Morgan Stanley
business will increase Chase Global Investor Services' assets under
trust and custody to more than $4.7 trillion, of which
approximately $1.8 billion will represent cross-border assets.
	   
</TEXT>
