Dollar higher, Gold up in London
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds:UPDATES with late rates &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar rose against major currencies in
late European trading Monday. Gold prices were higher.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _ 1.7800 German marks, up from 1.7740
	   _ 140.45 Japanese yen, up from 139.50
	   _ 1.4788 Swiss francs, up from 1.4750
	   _ 5.9680 French francs, up from 5.9479
	   _ 2.0065 Dutch guilders, up from 1.9990
	   _ 1,753.50 Italian lire, up from 1,745.90
	   _ 1.4587 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4593
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6311, down from dlrs
1.6356.
	   Gold in London closed at dlrs 292.15 per ounce, up from dlrs
291.40 bid late Friday.
	   In Zurich, the late bid price was dlrs 292.10, up from dlrs
291.40 late Friday.
	   Earlier in Hong Kong, gold fell dlrs 1.60 to close at dlrs
290.05 bid.
	   Silver closed in London at dlrs 5.30 a troy ounce, up from dlrs
5.22 a troy ounce Thursday.
	   (eml)
