<HEADLINE>
Evening of old favourites at classical music concert, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Evening of old favourites at classical music concert, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SILENCE accompanied the superb performance of the Selangor
Philharmonic Chamber Choir and the Selangor Philharmonic Choir at
the Kuala Lumpur City Hall auditorium in Jalan Raja Laut during the
Konsert Klasik Variasari recently.
	   Eyes intent, the audience seemed to be holding their breath
every time the choir rendered the songs. At the end of each song,
loud applause would follow.
	   The singers were accompanied by the Orkestra Kuala Lumpur under
the guest conductor Eprodito G. Bartolome.
	   The two choirs sang old favourites including Malam Ku Bermimpi,
Getaran Jiwa, Matona - Lovely Maiden, Dahil Sa Iyo, O La, O Che
Buon Eco and evergreens including In the Still of the Night,
Somewhere Out There and the Sound of Music.
	   The Selangor Philharmonic Chamber Choir was formed in 1996 and
consisted of 20 members. The choir specialised in singing acapella,
ranging from folk songs to modern arrangements.
	   The choir appeared for the first time in December 1996 when it
presented a selection of Christmas carols.
	   The Selangor Philharmonic Choir was set up in 1993 and appeared
for the first time in the Philharmonic Society's presentation of
Cavalleria Rusticana.
	   
</TEXT>
