<BODY>
<SLUG> PLDT-ANNOUNCES-LAUNCHING sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLDT Announces Launching Of Network Pilipinas, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
PLDT Announces Launching Of Network Pilipinas, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (PLDT) recently bared
details of its plan to implement a network computing infrastructure
in the Philippines called Phil-Net, first announced yesterday by
Antonio O. Cojuangco, PLDT President and CEO.
	   Robert R. Romulo, PLDT chair, said that Phil-Net which has been
renamed ''Network Pilipinas'' to avoid confusion with the
government-owned project PHNET has already begun implementation of
Phase I of the project. Phase I involves the linking up of
educational and technical institutions to a central repository
where they can share data without going through the internet.
	   Two schools are set to join the network -- Far Eastern
University (FEU) and the University of Asia and the Pacific (UA&AMP;P).
Lease line provisioning is already in place and the schools have
already chosen a place in their campuses to house the network
computers. Each school will have 40 Network Computers attached to a
Central Network Computer server located at PLDT.
	   This common network will be attached to Infocom to provide
internet connection including e-mail services and web development.
	   Phil-Net, signed exactly a year ago between Oracle Corp. Chair
and CEO Larry Ellison and PLDT Chair Roberto Romulo and witnessed
by President Fidel Ramos, aims to provide low-cost distribution
channel for information products and services and to provide a
backbone for members to share information with each other
independent of the Internet.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 BUSINESS DAILY all rights reserved as distributed
by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
