<HEADLINE>
Grand relaunch of tourism magazine, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Grand relaunch of tourism magazine, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   TO promote domestic tourism, a local travel, leisure and
lifestyle magazine, known as Mystical Malaysia was relaunched on
June 2 by the Minister of Culture, Arts and Tourism Datuk
Sabbaruddin Chik at the Kuala Lumpur Tower.
	   The magazine was first published in January 1988 and had won
awards for the ``Best Travel Publication'' and ``Best Travel
Writer'' at the Tourist Development Corporation's annual Tourism
Gold Awards.
	   The publication was stopped for five years and now, BN and
Associates has resumed its operations and the publishers are quite
confident of repeating the previous successes.
	   BN and Associates publisher Bernice Narayanan said the time was
right again to promote domestic tourism.
	   She said 10 years ago, the company focused on promoting the
country to the foreign tourists to visit Malaysia.
	   ``Now, times have changed. We have to promote domestic tourism
to our own people. We have so many beautiful places with rich
culture and heritage to visit,'' she said.
	   ``It is sad that most Malaysians do not visit the wonderful
places we have but prefer to travel overseas which they find
glamorous.''
	   She said the timing was right, in the light of the current
economic situation, to bolster the viability of locals travelling
within Malaysia as well as attracting foreign tourists to visit
Malaysia.
	   This time, however, the magazine will feature a revamped cover
design, giving it a more vibrant and modern appeal which will be
reflected in its use of design, layout and typeface.
	   Mystical Malaysia will feature articles on local cuisines,
nightspots, sports and recreation.
	   Bernice said the purpose was to make the magazine more
attractive to a wider audience.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
