<HEADLINE>
NCR Joins Visa Intl.'s Smart Initiative, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
NCR Joins Visa Intl.'s Smart Initiative, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   NCR Corp., one of the world's leading suppliers to the retail
financial services industry has signed a letter of intent to join
Visa International's Visa Smart initiative as part of NCR's
commitment to the fast-growing smart-card sector.
	   Visa Smart brings together NCR with other leading suppliers and
a comprehensive group of providers of chip-based products and
services to help Visa's member banks around the world launch smart
card programs quickly and cost-effectively.
	   The alliance with Visa, announced recently at the CardTech '98
show in Washington DC, further establishes NCR as a leading player
in the area of smart cards-chip-enabled bank cards that can store
electronic cash. The cards can be used to upload cash from a
variety of access points such as automated teller machines (ATMs)
and telephones. This electronic cash can then be used instead of
small change to buy goods and services ranging from food to
transport tickets and many other items.
	   NCR is already working with many banks around the world on their
smart-card solutions both by upgrading ATMs to take the new cares
and by integrating the transactions that flow from the cards into
banks' payments systems.
	   ``We're firm believers in the potential of smart cards and we're
proud to be part of the Visa Smart program,'' said Peta Matthews,
NCR's director of smart card programs. ``Over the next few years
we'll see many new smart-card applications that will both excite
consumers and offer new opportunities for banks.''
	   Visa is the largest consumer payment system worldwide with more
volume than all other major payment cards combined and has 21,000
member financial institutions. Visa has more than 70 smart card
programs in 30 countries and on the Internet, with 22 million Visa
chip cards, including eight million Visa Cash cards. Visa is
pioneering SET (Secure Electronic Transaction?) programs to enable
and advance Internet commerce.
	   
</TEXT>
