	   Exclusive Deal
	   The Business Daily is pleased to announce that as part of
continuing efforts to afford the best possible service to
subscribers and readers, TBD has entered into an exclusive
agreement with Los Angeles Times Syndicate and Review Publishing
Co. Ltd., publisher of Asia's business newsweekly, the Far Eastern
Economic Review (FEER).
	   Starting this month, FEER articles -- including cover stories --
will see print exclusively in TBD.
	   The agreement with FEER is a major development, coming on the
heels of another exclusive agreement signed in December last year
between TBD and The Washington Post Writers Group and Newsweek, the
international news magazine owned and operated by Newsweek Inc.,
New York.
	   Newsweek articles -- including cover stories from the news
magazine's different world editions (Atlantic, Pacific, Latin
American, US, UK editions) -- have since then been published
exclusively by TBD on a simultaneous-release basis.
	   The new agreement with FEER allows for transmission of stories
to TBD on Thursdays, the magazine's issue day, for use the next
day. Hence, TBD will print the cover story on Mondays and carry
FEER stories throughout the week.
	   Published weekly (every Thursday) in HK since 1946, FEER is
``the world authority on Asian current affairs, business, economics
and investment.''
	   Review Publishing Co. Ltd. is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Dow
Jones and Co. Inc.
	   
