	   IT will be the end of water woes for some 20 children of the
Ti-Ratana Welfare Society and they have to thank The Rotary Club of
Kuala Lumpur DiRaja.
	   The club, at its weekly meeting, donated two water tankers with
electrical pumps costing RM6,500 as part of its community service
project.
	   Present to receive the contribution from the club president
Jimmy Lim was Rev K. Dhamma Ratana.
	   The Ti-Ratana Welfare Centre located in Salak South Garden was
officially opened in June last year.
	   The society houses 20 children between the ages of three and 14
and has been managing its affairs through donations and its Sponsor
A Child Programme.
	   Ratana said the economic slowdown had significantly reduced
donation and the recent water rationing had affected the home
badly.
	   The Rotary Club of Kuala Lumpur DiRaja is the oldest and the
biggest of the Rotary Club in Malaysia with a membership of about
120.
	   During the weekly meeting, the club's very own website was
launched by Miss Malaysia/Universe 1998 Sherine Wong and Ms Tourism
1998 Ooi Bee Bee.
	   
