<HEADLINE>
Entertaining flick with Karthik at his best, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Entertaining flick with Karthik at his best, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   K.N. VijiyanASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE last time I saw Karthik was in Uthavikku Varalamah, another
of those movies which tries to solicit laughs by using the
``mistaken-identity''
	   formula.
	   There are a number of songs added to the tiresome fare although
you could not fault Karthik's acting in that movie. In Harichandra
(this one has nothing to do with the oldie with the same name),
Karthik is at his best in both comedy and drama.
	   Newcomer Cheyar Ravi shines in this truly entertaining movie.
	   Normally, you can predict how a story will go but here it is
totally unpredictable as director Cheyar Ravi surprises with new
elements. It was absolutely delightful until the end.
	   Harichandra, as you may know, is the name of a king who lived
long ago, who was known for his absolute honesty and morals.
	   Here, the hero of the movie, Harichandra (Karthik), is just the
opposite. He drinks, smokes and lies but in his parents' eyes, he
is the paragon of virtue.
	   Hari works in an advertising firm. While out shooting a
commercial, he chances upon Nandhini (Meena), a teacher. Hari falls
head over heels in love with her although his friends say she hates
those who smoke, drink or lie.
	   One lie leads to another and before Nandhini knows it, she is in
love with Hari.
	   But the lies begin to unravel and Hari has a tough time keeping
his girl.
	   Ravi ensures the songs (by newcomer Agoshi) do not interfere
with his story by pacing them at 40-minute intervals.
	   To satisfy action fans, a few fights have also been added but
they are necessary for the storyline. The cinematography by Ravi
Yadav and the art direction are a treat for the eyes.
	   Harichandra is one of the better movies this year after Ponmanam
and Thulli Thiruntha Kaalam. It has a good story, direction,
cinematography and fun.
	   It is now playing at the small cineplex in Wilayah Complex,
Kuala Lumpur. If you are patient, you may enjoy it better when it
plays at the bigger cineplexes or theatres in Klang.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
(PROFILE
(WS SL:ENTERTAINING-FLICK sked; CT:w; 
(REG:ENGL;)
