<SLUG> BC-Poland-Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Polish man kills three and commits suicide
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WARSAW, Poland (AP) _ A 60-year-old hunter shot and killed three
people during a party at his home in the southwestern city of Opole
Monday, then committed suicide, police said.
	   The man, whom police refused to identify, first started shooting
through the window, wounding four passers-by. Then, he shot and
killed three people inside his apartment and committed suicide,
according to police superintendent Andrzej Dabrowski of the Opole
provincial police headquarters.
	   He said the man was using a Polish-made TT revolver, once a
popular police weapon here.
	   Investigators were trying to establish identities of the victims
and of the gunman, as well as the motive for the murders, Dabrowski
said. No further details were available.
