<HEADLINE>
Club donates spectacles to underprivileged pupils, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Club donates spectacles to underprivileged pupils, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETALING JAYA, Fri. - Fifty-two underprivileged children will be
able to see a whole lot better, thanks to the generosity of the
Inner Wheel Club of Bangsar which donated spectacles worth RM2,000
to seven schools today.
	   The schools are Sekolah Rendah Kebangsaan Midlands Klang,
Sekolah Rendah Sea Port, Sekolah Rendah Kebangsaan Sri Kelana,
Sekolah Rendah Ladang Seafield, Sekolah Rendah Kebangsaan SS19
Subang Jaya, Sekolah Rendah Kebangsaan Castlefield and Sekolah
Rendah Kebangsaan Kinrara.
	   It also donated sports equipment worth about RM1,000 to Sekolah
Rendah Ladang Seafield.
	   Its president, Datin Naresh Kumari, said the schools' principals
took the children for eye check-ups two months ago.
	   ``About 100 pupils went and 52 of them were told they needed
glasses,''
	   she said.
	   Ten-year-old Marina Ramly, a recipient of a pair of spectacles,
said, ``I could not see the writing on the blackboard before. Now,
I am so glad as I will be able to see better.''
	   This sentiment was shared by R. Logeswari, also 10, who said
that she was ``very, very happy'' to receive the glasses.
	   The club, comprising wives, mothers and sisters of Rotary Club
members, have projects for the needy each year.
	   
</TEXT>
