	   THE Malaysian rubber market continued to weaken yesterday, as
trading remained lacklustre on lack of fresh leads.
	   ``Players are noticeably absent from the market awaiting
positive factors to emerge to spur the dull market,'' said a rubber
trader.
	   In addition, the local rubber is facing a stiff price
competition from neigbouring countries such as Thailand which is
offering cheap rubber in the international market, the trader said.
	   
