	   CRUDE palm oil (CPO) futures on the Kuala Lumpur Commodity
Exchange (KLCE) extended Thursday's gains due to technical buying
on the continued weak ringgit ahead of the weekend.
	   The market which opened encouragingly, gradually increased in
mid morning on technical buying when the ringgit weakened to 3.9950
against the US dollar.
	   It however, plunged sharply on profit taking in mid afternoon
which capped heavy gains.
	   Meanwhile, crude palm oil physicals finished higher on continued
weakening of the ringgit.
	   June-South surged RM5 to RM2,385 per tonne.
	   
