MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Q: COULD you give me a recipe for Mango Mousse Cake - mango
mousse atop a thin layer of cake? Also, how do you melt gelatine in
a microwave?
	   A: TO dissolve gelatine in the microwave, put three tablespoons
of cold water in a small microwaveable bowl and sprinkle over a
satchet of gelatine. Leave to soak for one minute until absorbed,
then microwave on full power for 30 seconds until hot but not
boiling. Stir until clear and dissolved. Leave to cool slightly
before using as required.
	   MANGO MOUSSE CAKE Sponge Base 2 large eggs 55g caster sugar 1/2
tsp vanilla essence 60g self-raising flour, sifted 1/2 tbsp
sunflower or corn oil 1/2 tbsp UHT or fresh milk 1-2 tbsp fresh
fruit juice Topping 15g gelatine 45ml water 200g ripe mango, diced
and pureed 50g sugar 1 tbsp lemon juice 200ml whipping cream,
whipped Sliced mango or passion fruit pulp, for decoration Prepare
Sponge Base Grease sides of a 21cm spring form pan and line the
base with non-stick parchment. Put eggs, caster sugar and vanilla
essence in a mixing bowl and whisk until thick and white.
	   Fold in self-raising flour. Stir in vegetable oil and milk.
	   Turn mixture into prepared pan and bake in centre of preheated
oven 190 degrees Celsius for 15 minutes or until firm and golden.
	   Remove from oven and cool before peeling off lining paper. Place
the cake back in the pan and sprinkle over the fruit juice.
	   Fresh or tinned juice such as orange or pineapple juice can be
added to moisten the cake. Now prepare the mousse topping.
	   Topping Soften the gelatine in the water and set bowl in a pan
of hot water.
	   Stir to dissolve gelatine and cool. Add gelatine to mango puree
with sugar and lemon juice. Stir well to mix evenly. Fold in the
whipped cream.
	   Pour mango mixture over the cake in the pan. Level the surface.
	   Refrigerate until set.
	   Place cake on serving dish and decorate the surface with sliced
mango or passion fruit pulp.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
