<HEADLINE>
Second seeded Clavet defeated at Bologna tennis
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with later matches, CORRECTS typo in Vicente, match
score &QL; 
 &UR; With BC-Sports-Tennis-Bologna, Results

<TEXT>
	   BOLOGNA, Italy (AP) _ No. 2 seed Francisco Clavet of Spain was
upset by Argentina's Franco Squillari 6-3, 4-6, 6-0 Monday in the
first round of the Carisbo international tennis tournament.
	   Clavet was one of a bevy of other Spaniards making an early exit
or advancing at the dlrs 340,000 clay court tournament.
	   Galo Blanco, seeded fourth, lost a hard-fought match against
Italy's Marzio Martelli, 7-5, 6-7, 6-4. Oliver Gross of Germany
defeated Fernando Vicente 6-4, 6-3 and Juan Albert Viloca beat
fellow Spaniard Oscar Serrano 6-3, 6-2.
	   On the other side of the ledger, Emilio Alvarez upset
seventh-seeded Brazilian Fernando Meligeni 7-5, 6-3 and Alex
Calatrava defeated Emanuel Couto of Portugal 7-5, 6-3.
	   In another match, Mariano Puerta of Argentina easily handled
Belgian Johan Van Herck, 6-3, 6-2.
	   The 32-draw tournament opened Monday, with the finals scheduled
for Sunday.
	   (tt/djw) 	   
