	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - Contributing to the excitement in the
run-up to the Commonwealth Games 1998, Basswinn Sales and Services
Sdn Bhd today launched a ``Name the Athletes'' contest featuring
five prominent Malaysian athletes who will be participating in the
Games.
	   The sole distributor of Siemens home appliances in Malaysia also
donated RM1,000 each to the Perak Amateur Swimmers Association, the
Malaysia Squash and Gymnastic Associations, Malaysian National
Cycling Federation and the Amateur Athletics Union.
	   At the launch at Siemens showroom in Jalan Ampang, Basswinn's
managing director Andrew Lye said the contest was aimed at
generating greater awareness of the Games among the public and to
enhance the feeling of commitment and participation in it.
	   ``At the same time, we need to give full encouragement to our
athletes who will be competing in the Games. Therefore we decided
to feature our leading athletes in the contest,'' he said.
	   In the contest which will run from June 8 to Aug 8, contestants
will have to identify the athletes whose faces are featured in the
contest forms which will be available in 660 EXB each.
	   Donations to the sports bodies were handed by Siemens Electrical
Engineering Sdn Bhd managing director Christian Urbanke to
representatives of the bodies which included national athletes M.
Kumaresan and Nur Herman Majid.
	   Siemens is one of the official sponsors of the Commonwealth
Games.
	   The launch also saw Basswinn's chairman Cindy Tan handing
contributions in the form of home appliances to representatives
from Shelter Home, Rumah Ozanam, Beautiful Gate Home, Rumah
Kanak-kanak Impian and Rumah Care.
	   
