	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - Hole-in-the-heart patient Wong San Choon
urgently needs RM22,000 to pay for surgery.
	   Doctors at the Gleneagles Intan Medical Centre in Jalan Ampang
diagnosed the four-and-a-half-year-old boy as suffering from a
ventricular septal defect.
	   His father, Wong Yit Wang, 43, from Muar, Johor, is a bus
conductor while his mother, Lim Shuat Keow, 34, is a housewife.
They have another child Bee Chin who is three.
	   Doctors said without surgery, San Choon will develop progressive
lung damage and have a short life.
	   Donations can be sent by way of crossed cheques payable to the
New Straits Times with San Choon's name written on the back, and
addressed to: Finance/Cashier, The New Straits Times Press (M) Bhd,
Balai Berita, 31 Jalan Riong, 59100 Kuala Lumpur.
	   
