<SLUG> SEARCH-OF-PERAK-MAN sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
350 gearing up for treasure hunt adventure in search of Perak Man, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
350 gearing up for treasure hunt adventure in search of Perak Man, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - About 350 participants in 100 vehicles will
be off ``In Search of the Perak Man'' - the theme of the National
Press Club-Lovan Treasure Hunt '98 on June 20.
	   In addition to top prizes, which include trips to Cairo and
Cebu, the Philippines, courtesy of Malaysia Airlines, participants
can also look forward to prizes in the numerous categories created
to make the event more enjoyable.
	   There are at least 10 categories, like the Most Sporting Team;
Most Adventurous Team; Deep Fried Team; Most Creative Team; Most
Innovative Team and the Most Organised Team.
	   Meal, entertainment, petrol vouchers and prizes aside, the
winning teams in each category will also walk away with Caltex
Havoline Formula 3 Motor Oil and brake fluid.
	   Caltex Malaysia managing director Robert J. Gregory today handed
over the company's sponsorship of 60 packs of four-litre
lubricants, 72 packs of brake fluid and 144 packs of battery water
to NPC president, Zainon Ahmad, at the NPC, Jalan Tangsi. Also
present was Caltex marketing director Khoo Thian Choe.
	   ``The treasure hunt gives the participants an opportunity to
explore places of archaeological interest,'' Gregory said, adding
it also helped build camaraderie among members of the Press.
	   Response towards the treasure hunt has been overwhelming with
the organisers having to turn down numerous entries.
	   ``We acheieved our target of 100 cars even before the closing
date of May 29,'' Zainon said.
	   The hunt will start at 7.30am at the Museum Negara carpark and
will finish at the Orient Star Lumut, Lumut, for an overnight stay
and prize presentation.
	   The hunt's main sponsor is Lovan Industries, a Penang-based
manufacturer of high quality hi-fi audio visual racks. In addition
to the RM70 Caltex petrol vouchers, the company is also giving 100
AV hi-fi racks. Bee Leong Industries is giving 200 vouchers
redeemable for its three ranges of knitwear - Rediscover, No Age
and Dinos.
	   Zaman Manufacturers is sponsoring an assortment of 200 export
quality travelling and sports bags while A. Clouet &AMP; Co (KL) Sdn
Bhd, distributor of Ayam Brand products, is providing sandwich
breakfast. Nestle is providing hot nescafe and cold Milo drinks.
	   Other sponsors to date include KTM Berhad, Mayban Finance;
Metroplex Holdings; Royal Selangor; Sunway Lagoon; Gillette
Malaysia; Maybank; KFC and Carlsberg.
	   Hawk Rent-A-Car Sdn Bhd is providing transport for all officials
involved in the treasure hunt.
	   Participants who have yet to be notified of their competition
numbers are urged to contact NPC secretaries at 03-7198195.
	   
</TEXT>
