	   SEREMBAN Views (NST, May 11) had much to say on uncollected
rubbish and dirty drains being in need of urgent attention by the
authorities.
	   It baffles me. How can ratepayers assist in keeping the
environment clean and tidy if necessary facilities and pro-active
action is lacking from the authorities.
	   As they say, it takes two to tango! There must be reciprocal
action by both, otherwise things end up much the same as before.
	   All must be seen to be involved in the final push to clean up
for the coming Commonwealth Games.
	   Otherwise, visitors will have much to comment on when they see
so much general uncleanliness. Let us keep our surroundings spick
and span for the big day.
	   Garbage is a dirty word. If there is a lack of bins or whatever,
get them and stop looking for excuses.
	   On a more positive note, I have noticed that the traffic problem
seems to have improved in town.
	   
