<BODY>
<SLUG> PATIMAS-COMPUTERS sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Patimas Computers to meet profit guarantee, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Patimas Computers to meet profit guarantee, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PATIMAS Computers Bhd, is confident it will be able to meet its
profit guarantee as stated in its prospectus despite the country's
slower economic growth, executive director Ng Back Heang said
yesterday.
	   Patimas Computers has guaranteed its shareholders it will be
able to secure 90 per cent of its forecast group pre-tax profit of
RM13.03 million for the year ending Dec 31, 1998.
	   Patimas Computers, which is listed on the second board of the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange is an investment holding company with
subsidiaries involved in providing software solutions and services.
	   It has subsidiaries in Singapore, Thailand, Indonesia,
Philippines and India.
	   Speaking after Patimas Computers' annual meeting in Bukit Jalil,
Selangor, Ng said the company hopes to register more than the
forecast figure for the year ending Dec 31, 1998.
	   ``Our business will not be affected by the economic slowdown as
it mainly provides software solutions to financial institutions and
manufacturing companies,'' executive director Dan E. Khoo said.
	   He said both the financial and manufacturing sectors were the
main contributors to total revenue of the country's information
technology industry.
	   ``Unless the companies and institutions close down or stop
operating, we will not be affected by the current economic problems
in the country.
	   ``The next 12 to 18 months are a crucial period for most
financial institutions and companies as they have to become year
2000 compliant,''
	   Khoo said.
	   Patimas recently secured two contracts - one from a company in
the United Kingdom and another from an American company.
	   It will be developing software-modules related to the automotive
industry for the UK-based information technology company.
	   And for the American company, it will develop modules related to
the manufacturing industry.
	   For the year ended Dec 31, 1997, Patimas Computers' group
pre-tax profit increased to RM11.28 million from RM8.77 million in
the previous corresponding period.
	   Turnover increased 47.5 per cent to RM84.10 million from RM57.04
million in 1996.
	   
</TEXT>
