<HEADLINE>
Southern Bank posts better results, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Southern Bank posts better results, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SOUTHERN Bank Bhd posted a 227 per cent increase in group
pre-tax profit for the financial quarter ended March 31, 1998 to
RM31.6 million from a loss of RM24.9 million previously.
	   At bank level, pre-tax rose by 157 per cent to RM42.2 million
compared with the previous quarter.
	   At group level, interest income increased by two per cent to
RM216.34 million from RM211.79 million previously.
	   Its interest income rose four per cent to RM188.65 million from
RM181.32 million previously.
	   Group loan loss and provisions charged to the profit and loss
account during the quarter amounted to RM23.15 million, a decrease
of RM25.0 million or 52 per cent over the preceding quarter of
RM48.17 million.
	   The bank's loan loss and provisions amounted to RM17.89 million,
a decrease of 45 per cent over the preceding quarter of RM32.65
million.
	   As at March 31, 1998, the bank's and group's risk weighted
capital ratio stood at 19.91 per cent and 21.93 per cent
respectively.
	   Shareholders' funds for the group stood at RM1.2 billion from
RM1.18 billion previously.
	   
</TEXT>
