<HEADLINE>
Zecon remains bullish, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Zecon remains bullish, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ZECON Engineering Bhd is still bullish on its business outlook
despite the economic downturn.
	   In his annual statement, executive chairman Zainal Abidin Ahmad
says the company will continue to seek out growth and to find ways
to achieve optimal returns.
	   ``We have identified various opportunities to enhance the group.
We are looking into new ventures with fresh approaches,'' he adds.
	   He also says that Zecon is pursuing turnkey construction
projects as well as those on a build-operate-transfer basis.
	   In addition, Zecon is still identifying land for real estate
development and to boost its landbank for further expansion in this
sector.
	   Zecon posted a higher group pre-tax profit of RM9.95 million for
the year ended December 31 1997, compared with RM8.52 million
previously.
	   However, turnover declined to RM100.24 million compared with
RM103.49 million before.
	   Profit after tax and minority interest dropped to RM5.61 million
compared with RM6.13 million the last time.
	   Earnings per share fell to 23.6 sen compared with 31.7 sen
previously.
	   
