<HEADLINE>
Regent makes move against nepotism, JAKARTA POST
</HEADLINE>
Regent makes move against nepotism, JAKARTA POST &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   JAKARTA POST
   INDONESIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Bogor Regent Eddie Yoso Martadipura has abruptly canceled the
appointment of his son-in-law Iskandar as the new head of the
town's planning agency, saying that the latter has not yet received
the governor's decree for the job.
	   Eddie was supposed to install Iskandar together with other
senior officers on Friday.
	   A day before the installation ceremony, dozens of local
businesspeople thronged into the council chamber, demanding the
cancellation of Iskandar's appointment as part of the reform
movement to end nepotistic practices.
	   According to the entrepreneurs, Iskandar was chosen for the
appointment by leapfrogging over the normal procedural
requirements.
	   The protesters also urged the councilors to probe the business
practices of Eddie's son, Dani, who they said was involved in a
series of megaprojects organized by the regency office.
	   The projects allegedly included the development of the Rp 1
billion new regency office complex at Cibinong, the Rp 1.3 billion
regent's official residence and the Rp 10 billion Islamic Center,
they were quoted by Antara as saying.
	   ``Almost all megaprojects here fall into the hands of Eddie's
son and relatives,'' said head of the Bogor chapter of the
Indonesian Employers Association (Apindo), Kaswarin.
	   The businesspeople also demanded that town council speaker Eso
Soekarso resign for his alleged collusion during his two five-year
terms with the Bogor regent. This reportedly made the council
unable to properly control the regency office's actions. (bsr)
	   
</TEXT>
