<HEADLINE>
Aris clinches second division title
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Aris Salonica beat Ethnikos Asteras
Kessariani 3-1 Monday to clinch the tough second division soccer
championship and return to the major league after one season.
	   After 34 rounds, Aris pilled up a total of 72 points.
	   In a game played over the weekend, Panelefsiniakos Elefsis beat
Anagenissi Karditsas 3-0 to finish the season second with 69 points
and return to the first division league after 30 years.
	   Ethnikos Asteras follows in third place with 67 points to
promote to the major league for the first time in the club's
72-year history.
	   The three clubs will replace Kalamata of the southern city with
the same name, Athinaikos Athens and Panachaiki Patras which were
relegated to the second division.
</TEXT>
