	   STATELY VISITOR ... Albert Laja, 11, had a memorable day
yesterday morning when the Yang di-Pertua Negeri Tun Ahmad Zaidi
Adruce Muhammad Noor visited the Sarawak Hospital in Kuching and
presented him a gift.
	   Albert's father Arthur Jilan, 40, was also present.
	   Ahmad Zaidi's visit to the children's ward and the presentation
of 100 gifts to the patients there were part of the activities
organised to celebrate the Yang di-Pertuan Agong Tuanku Ja'afar's
birthday.
	   He was accompanied by wife Toh Puan Rosmiati, Deputy Chief
Minister Datuk Dr George Chan Hong Nam, Tourism Minister Dr James
Masing and Assistant Minister in the Chief Minister's Office Datuk
Sharifah Mordiah Tuanku Fauzi.
	   Other activities included a tea party at the Astana hosted by
Ahmad Zaidi and attended by about 300 VIPs and dignitaries.
	   There was also the inaugural Friendship Games Carnival involving
four departments, namely the State Secretary's Office, Federal
Secretary's Office, the police and the army.
	   
