<HEADLINE>
Arus Murni makes RM121m pre-tax loss, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Arus Murni makes RM121m pre-tax loss, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ARUS Murni Corp Bhd fell into the red with a group pre-tax loss
of RM121.28 million for the financial year ended December 31 1997,
against a profit of RM924,000 in the previous year.
	   The poor performance was attributed to the significant losses
incurred by the group's wholly-owned subsidiary, Kumpulan Kewangan
Bersatu Bhd, due to a higher provision for non-performing loans
made by the company.
	   However, interest income for the year improved to RM249.82
million from RM53,000 the previous year.
	   Net loss for the year under review stood at RM67.18 million,
against a net income of RM55.78 million in 1996.
	   Meanwhile, after-tax loss for the year was at RM349.31 million
compared with a profit of RM6.64 million the last time around.
	   Loss per share for the year was at 235 sen against an earnings
of 117 sen in the previous year.
	   
</TEXT>
