	   THE Securities Commission (SC) has ordered stockbroking firm
Halim Securities to cease all securities trading activities from
June 8, following default proceedings taken by the Securities
Clearing Automated Network Services (SCANS).
	   The SC said that apart from the default in payment of RM9.67
million to SCANS, Halim Securities had also failed to meet the
minimum liquid funds requirement under Rule 17A of the Kuala Lumpur
Stock Exchange.
	   
