<HEADLINE>
Publicis And Hal Riney &AMP; Partners to Merge, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
Publicis And Hal Riney &AMP; Partners to Merge, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Publicis SA and Hal Riney &AMP; Partners (HR &AMP; P) of the US have
agreed to combine to form a global advertising partnership. This
was announced locally by Antonio R. Mercado, chair of Publicis
Philippines Inc.
	   The new name of Hal Riney &AMP; Partners will be Publicis-Hal Riney
&AMP; Partners.
	   ``This is a very potent creative partnership,'' Mercado said,
``because both agencies are known for their intense creativity.''
	   The combination will allow existing clients of both firms to
benefit from a global network of advertising, while maintaining a
strong local presence in each country. Both agencies are present in
64 countries and more than 100 cities internationally.
	   Maurice Levy, president and CEO of Publicis, said, ``The
rapprochement with Hal Riney and Partners is exactly what Publicis
was looking for to reinforce its position in the US: an agency with
strong beliefs, highly creative, delivering outstanding solutions
to their clients, and enjoying substantial growth in recent
years.''
	   He said the work done by HR &AMP; P is consistent with that of
Publicis', ``with the outstanding plus of the personality of Hal
Riney.''
	   Levy said Publicis-Hal Riney &AMP; Partners will run independently
from Publicis' other US operations, including Publicis-Bloom, which
has achieved remarkable growth in the last year.
	   Publicis' creative work and innovative approach has contributed
to the success of legendary brands throughout the world, including
such blue-chip names as Nestle, Lancome, Coca-Cola, Renault,
L'Oreal Granier, Whirlpool, Heineken, Sara-Lee, Allied-Domecq,
Siemens, Carrefour, British Airways, United Biscuits,
Hewlett-Packard, and Club Med. With billings of about $4.7 billion,
Publicis achieved a growth rate of 20% in billings and 40% in
operating profit last year.
	   Publicis-Hal Riney &AMP; Partners has offices in San Francisco,
Chicago, New York, and Atlanta. Among its larger clients are Saturn
Corp., Sprint PCS, First Union Corp., Mirage Resorts Inc., and
America West Airlines. 
</TEXT>
