<HEADLINE>
24-hour water cut in JB next week, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
24-hour water cut in JB next week, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   JOHOR BARU, Sat. - Johor Baru will be without water for 24 hours
next week when Syarikat Air Johor conducts commissioning work for
pipes along Jalan Susur 5 off Jalan Tun Abdul Razak.
	   SAJ district senior manager Zainuddin Md Ghazali said in a
statement that water supply would be interrupted from 10am on June
9 to 10am the following day.
	   He urged the public to store sufficient water.
	   The areas affected are from Larkin to Stulang. Places like
Tampoi, Taman Daya and Permas Jaya on the west and east sides of
the city will not be affected.
	   Among the buildings affected will be the State Secretariat
building at Bukit Timbalan and Johor Menteri Besar's residence -
Saujana.
	   The Aloha Condominium, Saujana Condominium, Landmark Building,
Plaza Kotaraya, Tropical Inn Hotel, Rasa Sayang Hotel, Public Bank
Building, Merlin Tower, Hospital Sultanah Aminah, Kebun Bunga
Istana, courthouse, the prison and the Best World Plaza wil also be
affected.
	   Other places affected are areas along Jalan Yahya Awal, Jalan
Tasik Utara, Jalan Kolam Air, Jalan Storey, Jalan Lumba Kuda, Jalan
Ah Siang, Jalan Air Molek, Jalan Ibrahim, Jalan Wong Ah Fook, Jalan
Bukit Cagar, Jalan Bukit Meldrum, Jalan Indraputera, Jalan Stulang
Laut, Jalan Kilat, Jalan Stulang Darat, Jalan Stulang Laut, Jalan
Pandan and Jalan Stulang.
	   
