<BODY>
<SLUG> PRIVATE-WATER-CRAFT sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Enactment to cover private water-craft users, too, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Enactment to cover private water-craft users, too, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PORT DICKSON, Sat. - Private water-craft users will not be
excluded from the Personal Water Craft Enactment expected to take
effect later this month.
	   Besides regulating seawater sports, the Enactment - passed by
the State Legislative Assembly last month to ensure the safety of
users and beach- goers - also includes similar activities on
rivers, reservoirs and lakes.
	   Menteri Besar Tan Sri Mohamad Isa Abdul Samad said: ``Private
users at popular beaches must realise they are also governed by the
enactment,'' he said after opening a new market here today.
	   He said the construction of various new resorts and marinas in
the district had recently attracted many water sport enthusiasts
from the Klang Valley and neighbouring States.
	   Any user found flouting the regulations under the enactment
could face a maximum RM5,000 fine or six-months jail or both.
	   The Enactment stipulates among others that all water sports
facility users must be 16 years old and above while those below
this age must be accompanied by an adult. The use of a life jacket
is compulsory.
	   The user is prohibited from consuming alcohol or medicines
before using the facilities as this may cause a lack of
concentration and even black- outs.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
