<HEADLINE>
Games of suspense, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Games of suspense, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Eric PerisASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   HAVE you watched children as they watch a game? They are a
picture of concentration and they abide by the rules. They cheer
for both sides of the team and they enjoy a good game.
	   When the situation is tense and a player makes a leap that could
result in a score, there is silence. Only after the point is scored
or missed would they all cheer.
	   But sometimes, one or two will be acting out the movements as
seen by the movement of the boy next to the one wearing a yellow
T-shirt in Failed Attempt.
	   The entry by Julian Pang Yau Chin of Penang shows a player
leaping up to get the ball. It is a tense moment and everyone is
watching. The ball has moved to the right. Perhaps just after this
there might have been cheers.
	   This game of volleyball is played under what looks like a
platform built on stilts. Julian has not given any details of the
picture. A strap tied between the two pools acts as the net. The
floor is wet. It looks more like a wharf where houses are built on
stilts. The angle taken helps one to see the whole game, court and
spectators. A good action shot.
	   Another game of volleyball comes from Omar Ismail of Ipoh. This
picture, taken in Pulau Pangkor, is also of a make-shift court on
the beach.
	   The poles are of bakau wood and from the looks of it, the net is
also a bakau pole tied across two poles. I believe some shirts are
also hanging across the pole, perhaps to act as a net.
	   The angle taken by Omar does not show much of the Alternative
Net as he calls it. Perhaps if he had moved more to the left or
right from where he was standing, we would get a clearer picture.
	   A few netball pictures were submitted. Most of them were
straight forward pictures. No action. Chong Wai Sun of Petaling
Jaya has captured a tense moment in Please Go In, just after the
player (GS) had shot the ball at the net. The ball is just at the
rim and the shooter is hoping it will get in. It is a good study of
concentration. Should the ball fail to enter, then the opponents
will have to take over and they must be at the ready.
	   The games for the last of the sports series are badminton, ping
pong and other indoor games.
	   The closing date is July 3. Please do not paste the film packet
on the back of the print as removing it may damage the picture. But
do write down your name and address clearly and don't forget the
coupon.
	   
</TEXT>
