Napocor Four Month Energy Sales Up 8.26%, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
Napocor Four Month Energy Sales Up 8.26%, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   State Run National Power Corp.(Napocor) said on friday energy
sales in the first four months of the year rose 8.26%to 11.950.3
gigawatt-hours(gwhs) from 11,038 gwhs in the year earlier period.
	   In a report, Napocor said actual sales exceeded the original
forecast of 11,696.4gwhs.
	   A gigawatt-hour is equivalent to one million kilowatt-hours.
Napocor is the country biggest supplier of electricity.
	   The firm currently services a total of 279 customers, made up
primarily of industries and electric utilities. Energy sales to
these customers totaled 36,442 gwh in 1997,up 2.6% over the 1996
figure of 33,381 gwh.
	   
</TEXT>
