	   HONG Kong stock brokers predict directionless trading this week
as investors shellshocked by negative news stick to the sidelines,
dealers said.
	   Stagnant trading on Friday ``is a sign of things to come,'' said
James Osborne of ING Barings.
	   ``In the short term there is no real reason to move so they will
sit on the sidelines and do nothing,'' the dealer said.
	   Dealers said the underlying sentiment in the market remained
highly negative on fears the local economy is on the brink of
recession this year and Wall Street may be in for a sharp
correction.
	   The key Hang Seng index fell fell 365.09 points or 4.1 per cent
during the week to 8,569.47 on Friday.
	   
