	   TT RESOURCES Bhd said its proposed subscription of 99,000 new
ordinary shares of US$1 each for US$99,000 cash, representing 99
per cent of the enlarged share capital of Goldale International Ltd
will pave the way for the company to be a long-term player in the
regional food and beverage, leisure and entertainment markets.
	   Goldale is an investment holding company limited by shares and
incorporated in the British Virgin Islands with an authorised share
capital of US$50,000 (US$1 &QC;  RM3.99) divided into 50,000 shares of
US$1 each and an issued and paid up share capital of US$1,000.
	   The company has two wholly owned subsidiaries, namely ACN
081684648 Pty Ltd and ACN 081684568 Pty Ltd.
	   ACN 081684648 Pty Ltd is a property investment company while ACN
081684568 Pty Ltd is involved in the hotel business.
	   TT Resources' proposed subscription is subject to the approval
of the Foreign Investment Review Board of Australia.
	   
