<SLUG> BC-Britain-People-Queen Elizabeth II </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Queen attends gala tribute to impressario
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Queen Elizabeth II joined celebrities Monday night
for a gala show celebrating the 30-year career of the producer
behind such megahits as ``Cats,'' ``Phantom of the Opera'' and
``Les Miserables.''
	   Accompanied by her husband, Prince Philip, the queen was
entertained by extracts from shows produced in London's West End
theater district by Sir Cameron Mackintosh which went on to conquer
the globe, making him one of Britain's most successful theatrical
producers.
	   The star-studded cast of ``Hey Mr. Producer!'' performing in
front of the queen, who was dressed in a pale green evening gown,
included Julie Andrews, Judi Dench and Elaine Page, who has starred
in several musicals.
	   ``Hey Mr. Producer!'' began with a flashback to the day, 43
years ago, when an 8-year-old Cameron attended his first show _
Julian Slade's Salad Days _ and was captivated for life by the
romance of the theater.
	   It proceeded through his career and featured songs which he
helped put on the stage, including ``Food, Glorious Food'' from
``Oliver!'' ``Memory'' from ``Cats'' and ``Send in the Clowns.''
	   ``It is so special that the queen also is in the audience,''
said Ivana Trump as the evening began. ``I saw her as she came in
and it was great. She looked grand. It was lovely.''
	   (er) 	   
</TEXT>
