<SLUG> BC-Sports-RugbyU-New Zealand-Team </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
All Blacks hedge on Lomu
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AUCKLAND, New Zealand (AP) _ All Blacks selectors have been
unable to split Jonah Lomu and Auckland teammate Joeli Vidiri for
the first test team to play England on June 20.
	   Lomu missed the Super 12 final and Monday's All Blacks trial
with injury and must prove his fitness in Saturday's match between
England and New Zealand A.
	   Canterbury's Mark Mayerhofler continued his fairytale rise when
he was named to make his debut in the center for the first test at
Carisbrook in Dunedin.
	   Auckland halfback Ofisa Tonu'u and Otago Highlanders hooker
Anton Oliver will start in their first full tests.
	   Otago's Taine Randell, as expected, has been named captain
following the retirement of Sean Fitzpatrick, with Auckland lock
Robin Brooke named vice captain.
	   Several of the All Blacks reserves, plus Lomu, have been named
in the New Zealand A team to play England.
	   All Blacks:
	   Christian Cullen, Jeff Wilson, Mark Mayerhofler, Jonah
Lomu/Joeli Vidiri, Walter Little, Andrew Mehrtens, Ofisa Tonu'u,
Taine Randell (captain), Josh Kronfeld, Ian Jones, Robin Brooke,
Michael Jones, Olo Brown, Anton Oliver, Craig Dowd. Reserves:
Lomu/Vidiri, Caleb Ralph, Carlos Spencer, Mark Robinson, Todd
Blackadder, Mark Carter, Blair Larsen, Carl Hoeft, Norm Hewitt. Two
reserves to be omitted.
 &UR; (tjh)	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Sports-RugbyU-New Zealand-Team; CT:s; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
