<TEXT>
	   The 54-year-old Abacha died a heart attack on Monday and his
body was shipped to his northern hometown of Kano, near the border
with Niger.
	   In life, Abacha gave little indication of plans for a successor
and even had his former deputy jailed and sentenced to death in
connection with an alleged coup plot.
	   The ruling military junta, apparently looking to avoid political
unrest in the wake of a perceived power vacuum quickly convened to
select Abacha's replacement.
